Function: int getRandom(int rangeLow, int rangeHigh) {
  double myRand = rand() / (1. + 2147483647);
  int range = rangeHigh - rangeLow + 1;
  int myRand_scaled = (myRand * range) + rangeLow;
  return myRand_scaled;
}

Function: bool wait_countDown(struct data_queue *sequence, struct data_channel *channel) {
  int i;
  for (i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
    if (sequence[i].waiting == 1)
      return 1;
  }
  for (i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
    if (channel[i].countDown > 0)
      return 1;
  }
  return 0;
}

Function: bool valid_move(char c, int x, int y) {
  bool valid = 1;
  int person, i;
  char letter[] = {'B', 'D', 'T', 'M'};
  for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
    if (c == letter[i]) {
      person = i;
    }
  }
  if (x < 0 || x > 4 || y < 0 || y > 4) {
    valid = 0;
  } else if (shared_t.map[x][y] == 'F' &&
             !(shared_t.carrot_holder_t[0] == person ||
               shared_t.carrot_holder_t[1] == person)) {
    valid = 0;
  } else if (shared_t.map[x][y] != 'C' && shared_t.map[x][y] != ' ' &&
             person != 3) {
    valid = 0;
  } else if ((shared_t.carrot_holder_t[0] == person ||
              shared_t.carrot_holder_t[1] == person) &&
             ((shared_t.carrot_t[0][0] == x && shared_t.carrot_t[0][1] == y) ||
              (shared_t.carrot_t[1][0] == x && shared_t.carrot_t[1][1] == y))) {
    valid = 0;
  }
  return valid;
}

    valid = 0;

      valid = 0;
    }

    valid = 0;
  }

Function: int check_person(int x, int y) {
  int id;
  char person = shared_t.map[x][y];
  if (person == 'B') {
    id = 0;
  } else if (person == 'D') {
    id = 1;
  } else if (person == 'T') {
    id = 2;
  } else if (person == 'M') {
    id = 3;
  } else {
    id = -1;
  }
  return id;
}

    return 1;
  else if (c == 'T')
    return 2;
  else if (c == 'M')
    return 3;
  else
    return -1;
}

Function: bool hasPerson(struct Workspace *map, int x, int y) {
  bool person = 0;
  if (map->pos[x][y] == 'B' || map->pos[x][y] == 'D' || map->pos[x][y] == 'M' ||
      map->pos[x][y] == 'T') {
    person = 1;
    printf("There is someone in the square, not moving.\n");
  }
  return person;
}

Function: bool invalidMountain(struct Workspace *map, int pos_x, int pos_y) {
  bool invalid = 0;
  if (pos_x == map->bun.pos_x && pos_y == map->bun.pos_y && !(map->bun.dead)) {
    invalid = 1;
  } else if (pos_x == map->tz.pos_x && pos_y == map->tz.pos_y &&
             !(map->tz.dead)) {
    invalid = 1;
  } else if (pos_x == map->tty.pos_x && pos_y == map->tty.pos_y &&
             !(map->tty.dead)) {
    invalid = 1;
  } else if (pos_x == map->mvin.pos_x && pos_y == map->mvin.pos_y) {
    invalid = 1;
  } else if (pos_x == map->fg1.pos_x && pos_y == map->fg1.pos_y &&
             map->fg1.available) {
    invalid = 1;
  } else if (pos_x == map->fg2.pos_x && pos_y == map->fg2.pos_y &&
             map->fg2.available) {
    invalid = 1;
  }
  return invalid;
}

Function: bool hasFlag(struct Workspace *map, int x, int y) {
  bool fg = 0;
  if (map->pos[x][y] == 'C') {
    fg = 1;
  }
  return fg;
}

Function: bool atMountain(struct Workspace *map, int x, int y) {
  bool mtn = 0;
  if ((map->mtn.pos_x == x) && (map->mtn.pos_y == y)) {
    mtn = 1;
  }
  return mtn;
}

Function: bool foundPersonhasFlag(struct Workspace *map) {
  if (map->mvin.tty && map->tty.hasFlag) {
    return 1;
  }
  if (map->mvin.bugs && map->bun.hasFlag) {
    return 1;
  }
  if (map->mvin.tz && map->tz.hasFlag) {
    return 1;
  }
  return 0;
}

Function: int getRandom(int rangeLow, int rangeHigh) {
  double myRand = rand() / (1. + 2147483647);
  int range = rangeHigh - rangeLow + 1;
  int myRand_scaled = (myRand * range) + rangeLow;
  return myRand_scaled;

Function: int CreateClone(struct data_clone **warrior) {

  printf("Please input the number of clones to spawn: ");
  scanf("%d", &n_clone);
  printf("Spawning %d clones...\n", n_clone);
  *warrior = malloc(n_clone * sizeof(struct data_clone));
  if (warrior == ((void *)0)) {
    printf("Does not have enough memory for allocation. Exiting program\n");
    exit(0);
  }
  return n_clone;
}

Function: bool hasBomb(struct Workspace *map, int x, int y) {

  if (map->pos[x][y] == 'B') {
    bmb = 1;
    printf("Bomb has been found, not moving.\n");

  return bmb;

Function: bool isValidMove(struct Workspace *map, int x, int y) {
  bool valid;
  if ((map->wall_e.pos_x + x >= 4) || (map->wall_e.pos_x + x) < 0) {
    valid = 0;
  } else if ((map->wall_e.pos_y + y >= 4) || (map->wall_e.pos_y + y < 0)) {
    valid = 0;
  } else if (hasBomb(map, map->wall_e.pos_x + x, map->wall_e.pos_y + y)) {
    valid = 0;
  } else {
    valid = 1;
    printf("Safe to move.\n");
  }
  return valid;
}

test3
Prediction: int isValidMove_name_conflict(struct bomb *bomb, int x, int y) {
  if (bomb->x + x < 0 || bomb->x + x > 3) {
    return 0;
  }
  if (bomb->y + y < 0 || bomb->y + y > 3) {
    return 0;
  }
  if (hasBomb(bomb, bomb->x + x, bomb->y + y)) {
    return 0;
  }
  puts("Safe to move.");
  return 1;
}

Function: bool hasGold(struct Workspace *map) {
  printf("Checking if gold is encountered.\n");
  updateWorkspace(map);
  int pos_x = map->wall_e.pos_x;
  int pos_y = map->wall_e.pos_y;
  if ((map->gb1.pos_x == pos_x) && (map->gb1.pos_y == pos_y) &&
      map->gb1.available) {
    printf("Found gold!\n");
    return 1;
  }
  if ((map->gb2.pos_x == pos_x) && (map->gb2.pos_y == pos_y) &&
      map->gb2.available) {
    printf("Found gold!\n");
    return 1;
  }
  printf("Gold not found.\n");
  return 0;
}

test3
Prediction: int hasGold_name_conflict(struct workspace *ws) {
  puts("Checking if gold is encountered.");
  updateWorkspace(ws);
  if (ws->player.x == ws->gold1.x && ws->player.y == ws->gold1.y &&
      ws->gold1.visible) {
    puts("Found gold!");
    return 1;
  }
  if (ws->player.x == ws->gold2.x && ws->player.y == ws->gold2.y &&
      ws->gold2.visible) {
    puts("Found gold!");
    return 1;
  }
  puts("Gold not found.");
  return 0;
}

Function: int getRandom(int rangeLow, int rangeHigh) {
  double myRand = rand() / (1. + 2147483647);
  int range = rangeHigh - rangeLow + 1;
  int myRand_scaled = (myRand * range) + rangeLow;
  return myRand_scaled;
}

Function: bool foundGold(struct Workspace *map) {
  printf("Checking if gold is encountered.\n");
  updateWorkspace(map);
  int pos_x = map->wall_e.pos_x;
  int pos_y = map->wall_e.pos_y;
  if ((map->gb1.pos_x == pos_x) && (map->gb1.pos_y == pos_y) &&
      map->gb1.available) {
    printf("Found gold!\n");
    return 1;
  }
  if ((map->gb2.pos_x == pos_x) && (map->gb2.pos_y == pos_y) &&
      map->gb2.available) {
    printf("Found gold!\n");
    return 1;
  }
  printf("Gold not found.\n");
  return 0;
}

test3
Prediction: int foundGold_name_conflict(struct workspace *ws) {
  puts("Checking if gold is encountered.");
  updateWorkspace(ws);
  if (ws->player.x == ws->gold1.x && ws->player.y == ws->gold1.y &&
      ws->gold1.visible) {
    puts("Found gold!");
    return 1;
  }
  if (ws->player.x == ws->gold2.x && ws->player.y == ws->gold2.y &&
      ws->gold2.visible) {
    puts("Found gold!");
    return 1;
  }
  puts("Gold not found.");
  return 0;
}

Function: int getRandom(int rangeLow, int rangeHigh) {
  double myRand = rand() / (1. + 2147483647);
  int range = rangeHigh - rangeLow + 1;
  int myRand_scaled = (myRand * range) + rangeLow;
  return myRand_scaled;
}

Function: bool foundGold(struct Workspace *map) {
  printf("Checking if gold is encountered.\n");
  updateWorkspace(map);
  int pos_x = map->wall_e.pos_x;
  int pos_y = map->wall_e.pos_y;
  if ((map->gb1.pos_x == pos_x) && (map->gb1.pos_y == pos_y) &&
      map->gb1.available) {
    printf("Found gold!\n");
    return 1;
  }
  if ((map->gb2.pos_x == pos_x) && (map->gb2.pos_y == pos_y) &&
      map->gb2.available) {
    printf("Found gold!\n");
    return 1;
  }
  printf("Gold not found.\n");
  return 0;
}

test3

  updateWorkspace(ws);
  if (ws->player.x == ws->gold1.x && ws->player.y == ws->gold1.y &&
      ws->gold1.visible) {
    puts("Found gold!");
    return 1;
  }
  if (ws->player.x == ws->gold2.x && ws->player.y == ws->gold2.y &&
      ws->gold2.visible) {
    puts("Found gold!");
    return 1;
  }
  puts("Gold not found.");
  return 0;
}

Function: compare_t DescendingOrder(unsigned int left, unsigned int right) {
  compare_t ret;
  if (left == right)
    ret = Tie_e;
  else if (left > right)
    ret = LeftWins_e;
  else if (left < right)
    ret = RightWins_e;
  return ret;
}

test3
Prediction: int DescendingOrder_name_conflict(int a, int b) {
  int result;

  if (a == b) {
    result = 0;
  } else if (a > b) {
    result = 1;
  } else if (a < b) {
    result = 2;
  }

  return result;
}

Function: compare_t AscendingOrder(unsigned int left, unsigned int right) {
  compare_t ret;
  if (left == right)
    ret = Tie_e;
  else if (left > right)
    ret = RightWins_e;
  else if (left < right)
    ret = LeftWins_e;
  return ret;
}

Function: int cycle(int a) {
  int n = 1;
  while (a != 1) {
    if (a % 2) {
      a = 3 * a + 1;
    } else {
      a /= 2;
    }
    n++;
  }
  return n;
}

  while (n != 1) {
    if (n % 2 == 0) {
      n /= 2;
    } else {
      n = 3 * n + 1;
    }
    c++;
  }
  return c;
}

Function: int prime(int input) {
  if (input < 2)
    return 0;
  else {
    int i;
    for (i = 2; i < input; i++) {
      if (input % i == 0) {
        return 0;
      }
    }
    return 1;
  }
}

  int i;
  if (n < 2)
    return 0;
  for (i = 2; i < n; i++)
    if (n % i == 0)
      return 0;
  return 1;
}

Function: char *count_digits(int num, unsigned int count[]) {
  while (num != 0) {
    count[num % 10] += 1;
    num /= 10;
  }

Function: char *reverse(char *s) {
  register char t, *p = s, *q = (s + (strlen(s) - 1));
  while (p < q) {
    t = *p;
    *p++ = *q;
    *q-- = t;
  }
  return (s);
}

Function: int *merge(int *a, int *b, int s1, int s2) {
  int i, j, k;
  int *arr;
  int size = s1 + s2;
  arr = (int *)malloc(sizeof(int) * (size));
  for (k = 0, j = 0, i = 0; i <= size; i++) {
    if (a[k] < b[j]) {
      arr[i] = a[k];
      k++;
      if (k >= s1) {
        for (i++; j < s2; j++, i++)
          arr[i] = b[j];
      }
    } else {
      arr[i] = b[j];
      j++;
      if (j >= s2) {
        for (i++; k < s1; k++, i++)
          arr[i] = a[k];
      }
    }
  }
  return arr;
}

test3
Prediction: int *merge_name_conflict(int *a, int *b, int a_size, int b_size) {
  int *c = malloc(sizeof(int) * (a_size + b_size));
  int i = 0, j = 0, k = 0;
  while (k <= a_size + b_size) {
    if (a[i] < b[j]) {
      c[k] = a[i];
      i++;
      if (i >= a_size) {
        for (k++; j < b_size; j++, k++)
          c[k] = b[j];
      }
    } else {
      c[k] = b[j];
      j++;
      if (j >= b_size) {
        for (k++; i < a_size; i++, k++)
          c[k] = a[i];
      }
    }
    k++;
  }
  return c;
}

Function: int lawOfSines(side, angleA, angleC)
int side;
int angleA;
int angleC;
{
  int newSide;
  newSide = side * (sin((angleA * 3.1400000000000001) / 180)) /
            sin((angleC * 3.1400000000000001) / 180);
  return abs(newSide);
}

             sin(c * 3.14159265358979323846 / 180);
  return x > 0 ? x : -x;
}

Function: int ThirdAngleCalc(angleA, angleB)
int angleA;
int angleB;
{
  int angleC;
  angleC = (180 - (angleA + angleB));
  return angleC;
}

Function: int SAS() {
  int angleA;
  int angleB;
  int angleC;
  int sidea;
  int sideb;
  int sidec;
  int hold;
  puts("Enter your first angle:");
  scanf(" %d", &angleA);
  puts("Enter your first side:");
  scanf(" %d", &sideb);
  puts("Enter your second side:");
  scanf(" %d", &sidec);
  if (sideb > sidec) {
    hold = sidec;
    sidec = sideb;
    sideb = hold;
  }
  sidea = sqrt(
      (sideb * sideb) + (sidec * sidec) -
      ((2 * sideb * sidec) * (cos((3.1400000000000001 / 180) * (angleA)))));
  angleB =
      (180 / 3.1400000000000001) *
      (asin(((sin((3.1400000000000001 / 180) * (angleA)) * sideb) / sidea)));
  angleC = 180 - (angleA + angleB);
  drawing(sidea, sideb, sidec, angleA, angleB, angleC);
}

test3
Prediction: void SAS_name_conflict() {
  int a, b, c, A, B, C;
  double d;
  puts("Enter your first angle:");
  scanf("%d", &A);
  puts("Enter your first side:");
  scanf("%d", &a);
  puts("Enter your second side:");
  scanf("%d", &b);
  if (a < b) {
    c = a;
    a = b;
    b = c;
  }
  c = sqrt(a * a + b * b - 2 * a * b * cos(A * 3.14159265358979323846 / 180));
  B = asin(a * sin(A * 3.14159265358979323846 / 180) / c) * 180 /
      3.14159265358979323846;
  C = 180 - A - B;
  drawing(a, b, c, A, B, C);
}

Function: int SSS() {
  float angleA;
  float angleB;
  float angleC;
  float sidea;
  float sideb;
  float sidec;
  puts("Enter your first side:");
  scanf(" %f", &sidea);
  puts("Enter your second side:");
  scanf(" %f", &sideb);
  puts("Enter your third side:");
  scanf(" %f", &sidec);
  angleA = (180 / 3.1400000000000001) *
           acos((((sideb * sideb) + (sidec * sidec)) - (sidea * sidea)) /
                (2 * sideb * sidec));
  angleB = (180 / 3.1400000000000001) *
           acos((((sidec * sidec) + (sidea * sidea)) - (sideb * sideb)) /
                (2 * sidec * sidea));
  angleC = ThirdAngleCalc((int)angleA, (int)angleB);
  drawing((int)sidea, (int)sideb, (int)sidec, (int)angleA, (int)angleB,
          (int)angleC);
}

test3

  float a, b, c, A, B, C;
  puts("Enter your first side:");
  __isoc99_scanf("%f", &a);
  puts("Enter your second side:");
  __isoc99_scanf("%f", &b);
  puts("Enter your third side:");
  __isoc99_scanf("%f", &c);
  A = acos((b * b + c * c - a * a) / (2 * b * c)) * 180 /
      3.14159265358979323846;
  B = acos((a * a + c * c - b * b) / (2 * a * c)) * 180 /
      3.14159265358979323846;
  C = ThirdAngleCalc(a, b, c);
  drawing(a, b, c, A, B, C);
}

Function: int drawing(sidea, sideb, sidec, angleA, angleB, angleC)
int sidea;
int sideb;
int sidec;
int angleA;
int angleB;
int angleC;
{
  printf("Your sides are:\t %d \t %d \t %d \n", sidea, sideb, sidec);
  printf("And your angles are:\t %d \t %d \t %d \n", angleA, angleB, angleC);
  if (sidea == sideb && sideb == sidec) {
    puts("You made an equillateral triangle!");
  } else if (angleA == 90 || angleB == 90 || angleC == 90) {
    puts("You made a right triangle!");
  } else if (angleA == angleB || angleB == angleC || angleC == angleA) {
    puts("You made an isoceles triangle!");
  } else if (sidea != sideb && sideb != sidec && sidec != sidea) {
    puts("You made a scalene triangle!");
  }
}

test3
Prediction: void drawing_name_conflict(int a, int b, int c, int A, int B, int C) {
  printf("Your sides are:\t %d \t %d \t %d \n", a, b, c);
  printf("And your angles are:\t %d \t %d \t %d \n", A, B, C);

  if (a == b && b == c)
    printf("You made an equillateral triangle!\n");
  else if (A == 90 || B == 90 || C == 90)
    printf("You made a right triangle!\n");
  else if (A == B || B == C || C == A)
    printf("You made an isoceles triangle!\n");
  else if (a != b && b != c && c != a)
    printf("You made a scalene triangle!\n");
}

Function: int get_huxi(char *cards) {
  int huxi = get_kan_huxi(cards);
  int sum = 0;
  for (int i = 0; i < 20; i++) {
    sum += cards[i];
  }
  if (sum % 3 == 0) {
    int other_huxi = get_shun_huxi_xiao(cards);
    if (other_huxi < 0) {
      return -1;
    }
    return huxi + other_huxi;
  }
  int max_huxi = -1;
  char tmp_cards[20];
  for (int i = 0; i < 20; i++) {
    if (cards[i] != 2)
      continue;
    memcpy(tmp_cards, cards, 20);
    tmp_cards[i] -= 2;
    int other_huxi = get_shun_huxi_xiao(tmp_cards);
    if (other_huxi > max_huxi)
      max_huxi = other_huxi;
  }
  if (max_huxi < 0)
    return -1;
  return max_huxi + huxi;
}

Function: int get_kan_huxi(char *cards) {
  int huxi = 0;
  for (int i = 0; i < 10; ++i) {
    if (cards[i] != 3)
      continue;
    cards[i] = 0;
    huxi += 3;
  }
  for (int i = 10; i < 20; ++i) {
    if (cards[i] != 3)
      continue;
    cards[i] = 0;
    huxi += 6;
  }
  return huxi;
}

Function: int get_shun_huxi_xiao(char *cards) {
  struct Item items[7];
  memset(items, 0, sizeof(items));
  int cur_card = 0;
  int cur_item = -1;
  int find = 1;
  int max_huxi = -1;
  while (1) {
    if (find) {
      find = 0;
      int finded = 0;
      if (cur_item == 7) {
        *(int *)0 = 0;
      }
      for (int i = cur_card; i < 10; i++) {
        if (cards[i] != 0) {
          cur_card = i;
          ++cur_item;
          items[cur_item].card = cur_card;
          finded = 1;
          break;
        }
      }
      if (finded == 0) {
        int huxi = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i <= cur_item; ++i) {
          huxi += items[i].huxi;
        }
        int da_huxi = get_shun_huxi_da(cards);
        if (da_huxi >= 0) {
          if (da_huxi + huxi > max_huxi) {
            max_huxi = da_huxi + huxi;
          }
        }
        goto huisu;
      }
    }
    if (items[cur_item].i == 0) {
      items[cur_item].i = 1;
      if (cur_card < 8 && cards[cur_card + 1] > 0 && cards[cur_card + 2] > 0) {
        items[cur_item].j = 1;
        items[cur_item].card = cur_card;
        --cards[cur_card];
        --cards[cur_card + 1];
        --cards[cur_card + 2];
        find = 1;
        if (cur_card == 0) {
          items[cur_item].huxi = 3;
        }
        continue;
      }
    }
    if (items[cur_item].i == 1) {
      items[cur_item].i = 2;
      if (cards[cur_card] == 2 && cards[cur_card + 10] >= 1) {
        items[cur_item].j = 2;
        cards[cur_card] -= 2;
        --cards[cur_card + 10];
        find = 1;
        continue;
      }
    }
    if (items[cur_item].i == 2) {
      items[cur_item].i = 3;
      if (cards[cur_card + 10] == 2) {
        items[cur_item].j = 3;
        cards[cur_card + 10] -= 2;
        --cards[cur_card];
        find = 1;
        continue;
      }
    }
    if (items[cur_item].i == 3) {
      items[cur_item].i = 4;
      if (cur_card == 1 && cards[6] > 0 && cards[9] > 0) {
        items[cur_item].j = 4;
        items[cur_item].huxi = 3;
        find = 1;
        --cards[1];
        --cards[6];
        --cards[9];
        continue;
      }
    }
  huisu:
    if (cur_item < 0)
      goto finish;
    if (items[cur_item].i == 0 ||
        (items[cur_item].i == 4 && items[cur_item].j != 4)) {
      memset(&items[cur_item], 0, sizeof(struct Item));
      if (cur_item == 0)
        goto finish;
      --cur_item;
      goto huisu;
    }
    cur_card = items[cur_item].card;
    if (items[cur_item].i > 0 && items[cur_item].i == items[cur_item].j) {
      items[cur_item].huxi = 0;
      if (items[cur_item].j == 1) {
        ++cards[cur_card];
        ++cards[cur_card + 1];
        ++cards[cur_card + 2];
      } else if (items[cur_item].j == 2) {
        cards[cur_card] += 2;
        ++cards[cur_card + 10];
      } else if (items[cur_item].j == 3) {
        cards[cur_card + 10] += 2;
        ++cards[cur_card];
      } else if (items[cur_item].j == 4) {
        ++cards[1];
        ++cards[6];
        ++cards[9];
        memset(&items[cur_item], 0, sizeof(struct Item));
        if (cur_item == 0)
          goto finish;
        --cur_item;
        goto huisu;
      }
    }
  }
finish:
  return max_huxi;
}

Function: int get_shun_huxi_da(char *cards) {
  if (cards[10] > cards[11] || cards[10] > cards[12])
    return -1;
  int sum = 0;
  for (int i = 10; i < 20; ++i) {
    sum += cards[i];
  }
  if (sum == 0) {
    return 0;
  }
  char tmp_cards[10];
  memcpy(tmp_cards, &cards[10], 10);
  int n_123 = tmp_cards[0];
  tmp_cards[0] = 0;
  tmp_cards[1] -= n_123;
  tmp_cards[2] -= n_123;
  int max_huxi = -1;
  for (int i = 0; i < 5; ++i) {
    memcpy(tmp_cards, &cards[10], 10);
    tmp_cards[0] = 0;
    tmp_cards[1] -= n_123;
    tmp_cards[2] -= n_123;
    if (tmp_cards[1] < i || tmp_cards[6] < i || tmp_cards[9] < i) {
      break;
    }
    int huxi = get_shun_huxi_da_without_2_7_10(tmp_cards, i);
    if (huxi < 0)
      continue;
    if (huxi + n_123 * 6 > max_huxi)
      max_huxi = huxi + n_123 * 6;
  }
  return max_huxi;
}

Prediction: int get_shun_huxi_da_without_2_7_10(char *p, int da) {
  int i, j, k, l, m, n, o, p, q, r, s, t, u, v, w, x, y, z;
  int sum, max, temp;

  if (p[10] > p[11] || p[12] > p[11])
    return -1;

  sum = 0;
  for (i = 10; i < 19; i++)
    sum += p[i];

  if (sum == 0)
    return 0;

  max = -1;
  for (i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
    for (j = 0; j < 3; j++) {
      if (p[11] - i < 0 || p[11] - i < i)
        return max;
      if (p[14] - i < 0 || p[14] - i < i)
        return max;
      if (p[16] - i < 0 || p[16] - i < i)
        return max;
    }

    temp = get_shun_huxi_da_without_2_7_10(p, i);
    if (temp >= 0) {
      if (temp + i * 6 > max)
        max = temp + i * 6;
    }
  }

  return max;
}

Function: int get_shun_huxi_da_without_2_7_10(char *cards, int num) {
  char tmp_cards[10];
  memcpy(tmp_cards, cards, 10);
  tmp_cards[1] -= num;
  tmp_cards[6] -= num;
  tmp_cards[9] -= num;
  for (int i = 0; i < 10; ++i) {
    int n = tmp_cards[i];
    if (n == 0)
      continue;
    if (i + 2 >= 10)
      return -1;
    if (tmp_cards[i + 1] < n || tmp_cards[i + 2] < tmp_cards[i + 1])
      return -1;
    tmp_cards[i + 1] -= n;
    tmp_cards[i + 2] -= n;
  }
  return num * 6;
}

Prediction: int get_shun_huxi_da_without_2_7_10_name_conflict(const int *hand, int num) {
  int i;
  int count = 0;
  int temp[6];

  temp[0] = hand[0] / 256;
  temp[1] = hand[0] / 4096;
  temp[2] = hand[1] / 256;

  for (i = 0; i < 6; i++) {
    if (temp[i] == 0)
      continue;
    if (i >= 7)
      return -1;
    if (temp[i] > temp[i + 1] || temp[i] > temp[i + 2])
      return -1;
    temp[i + 1] -= temp[i];
    temp[i + 2] -= temp[i];
    count++;
  }

  return count * num;
}

Function: int binsearch(int x, int v[], int n) {
  int low, mid, high;
  low = 0;
  high = n - 1;
  while (low <= high) {
    mid = (low + high) / 2;
    if (x < v[mid])
      high = mid - 1;
    else if (x > v[mid])
      low = mid + 1;
    else
      return mid;
  }
  return -1;
}

Function: int binsearch2(int x, int v[], int n) {
  int low, high, mid;
  low = 0;
  high = n - 1;
  mid = (low + high) / 2;
  while (low <= high && x != v[mid]) {
    if (x < v[mid])
      high = mid - 1;
    else
      low = mid + 1;
    mid = (low + high) / 2;
  }
  if (x == v[mid])
    return mid;
  else
    return -1;
}

Function: int binsearch(int x, int v[], int n) {
  int low, high, mid;
  low = 0;
  high = n - 1;
  while (low < high) {
    mid = (low + high) / 2;
    if (x <= v[mid])
      high = mid;
    else
      low = mid + 1;
  }
  return (x == v[low]) ? low : -1;
}

Function: int binsearch(int x, int v[], int n) {
  int low, mid, high;
  low = 0;
  high = n - 1;
  while (low <= high) {
    mid = (low + high) / 2;
    if (x < v[mid])
      high = mid - 1;
    else if (x > v[mid])
      low = mid + 1;
    else
      return mid;
  }
  return -1;
}

  int low, high, mid;

  low = -1;
  high = n;
  while (low + 1 < high) {
    mid = (low + high) / 2;
    if (x > v[mid])
      low = mid;
    else
      high = mid;
  }
  if (high == n || x != v[high])
    return -1;
  else
    return high;
}

Function: int binsearch2(int x, int v[], int n) {
  int low, high, mid;
  low = -1;
  high = n;
  while (low + 1 < high) {
    mid = (low + high) / 2;
    if (v[mid] < x)
      low = mid;
    else
      high = mid;
  }
  if (high == n || v[high] != x)
    return -1;
  else
    return high;
}

Function: int can_print(int ch) {
  char *printable = "abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ123456"
                    "7890 !\"#%&'()*+,-./:;<=>?[\\]^_{|}~\t\f\v\r\n";
  char *s;
  int found = 0;
  for (s = printable; !found && *s; s++) {
    if (*s == ch) {
      found = 1;
    }
  }
  return found;
}

Function: char *char_in_string(char *s, int c) {
  char *p = ((void *)0);
  if (s != ((void *)0)) {
    if (c) {
      while (*s && *s != c) {
        ++s;
      }
      if (*s == c) {
        p = s;
      }
    }
  }
  return p;
}

test3

      ;
    if (*p == c)
      return p;
  }
  return NULL;
}

Function: char *tokenise(char **s, char *delims) {
  char *p = ((void *)0);
  char *q = ((void *)0);
  if (s && *s && delims) {
    while (((void *)0) != char_in_string(delims, **s)) {
      ++*s;
    }
    if (**s) {
      q = *s + 1;
      p = *s;
      while (*q && ((void *)0) == char_in_string(delims, *q)) {
        ++q;
      }
      *s = q + (*q != '\x00');
      *q = '\x00';
    }
  }
  return p;
}

test3
Prediction: char *tokenise_name_conflict(char **str, const char *delim) {
  char *ret = NULL;

  if (str && *str && delim) {
    while (char_in_string(delim, **str))
      (*str)++;

    if (**str) {
      char *p = *str;

      ret = *str;

      while (*++p && !char_in_string(delim, *p))
        ;

      *str = p + (*p != '\0');
      *p = '\0';
    }
  }

  return ret;
}

Function: int NoiseWord(char *s) {
  int found = 0;
  int giveup = 0;
  char *list[] = {"a",   "an", "and", "be", "but", "by",   "he", "I",
                  "off", "on", "she", "so", "the", "they", "you"};
  int top = sizeof list / sizeof list[0] - 1;
  int bottom = 0;
  int guess = top / 2;
  int diff = 0;
  if (s) {
    while (!found && !giveup) {
      diff = strcmp(list[guess], s);
      if (0 == diff) {
        found = 1;
      } else if (0 < diff) {
        top = guess - 1;
      } else {
        bottom = guess + 1;
      }
      if (top < bottom) {
        giveup = 1;
      } else {
        guess = (top + bottom) / 2;
      }
    }
  }
  return found;
}

test3
Prediction: int NoiseWord_name_conflict(char *word) {
  int found = 0;
  int notfound = 0;
  int cmp;
  int low = 0;
  int high = 14;
  int mid = (low + high) / 2;
  char *words[15] = {"a",   "an", "and", "are",  "as",   "at",
                     "be",  "by", "for", "from", "has",  "he",
                     "in",  "is", "it",  "of",   "on",   "that",
                     "the", "to", "was", "were", "will", "with"};

  if (word == NULL)
    return 0;

  while (!found && !notfound) {
    cmp = strcmp(words[mid], word);
    if (cmp == 0)
      found = 1;
    else if (cmp > 0)
      high = mid - 1;
    else
      low = mid + 1;

    if (low > high)
      notfound = 1;
    else
      mid = (low + high) / 2;
  }

  return found;
}

Function: enum token getword(char *word, int lim) {
  int beg_line, c;
  for (;;) {
    beg_line = skipws();
    c = getch();
    if (!beg_line || c != '#')
      break;
    do {
      c = getch();
      if (c == (-1))
        return TOK_EOF;
    } while (c != '\n');
    ungetch('\n');
  }
  if (c == (-1))
    return TOK_EOF;
  else if (c == '_' || ((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)(((unsigned char)c))] &
                        (unsigned short)_ISalpha)) {
    do {
      putch(&word, &lim, c);
      c = getch();
    } while (((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)(((unsigned char)c))] &
              (unsigned short)_ISalnum) ||
             c == '_');
    ungetch(c);
    return TOK_ID;
  } else if (c == '\'' || c == '"') {
    int quote = c;
    word[0] = '\x00';
    while (getstelem(&word, &lim, quote))
      ;
    return quote == '\'' ? TOK_CHAR : TOK_STRING;
  } else
    return (unsigned char)c;
}

test3
Prediction: int getword_name_conflict(char *word, int lim) {
  int c, getch(void);
  void ungetch(int);
  int skipws(void);

  while (skipws()) {
    c = getch();
    if (c == '#') {
      while ((c = getch()) != EOF && c != '\n')
        ;
      if (c == EOF)
        return 259;
      ungetch(c);
    } else if (c == EOF)
      return 259;
    else if (isalpha(c) || c == '_' || c == '"' || c == '\'')
      break;
    else
      return c;
  }

  if (c == EOF)
    return 259;

  if (isalpha(c) || c == '_') {
    do {
      putch(word, lim, c);
      c = getch();
    } while (isalnum(c) || c == '_');
    ungetch(c);
    return 256;
  }

  if (c == '"' || c == '\'') {
    int quote = c;
    *word = '\0';
    while (getstelem(&word, &lim, quote))
      ;
    if (quote == '\'')
      return 258;
    return 257;
  }

  return c;
}

Function: static int skipws(void) {
  enum class {
    CLS_WS = 0,
    CLS_BEG_CMT,
    CLS_END_CMT,
    CLS_OTHER,
    CLS_IN_CMT = 4
  };
  enum class in_comment = 0;
  int beg_line = 0;
  for (;;) {
    int c;
    enum class class;
    c = getch();
    switch (c) {
    case '\n':
      if (!in_comment)
        beg_line = 1;
    case ' ':
    case '\f':
    case '\r':
    case '\t':
    case '\v':
      class = CLS_WS;
      break;
    case '/':
      if (!in_comment) {
        c = getch();
        if (c == '*')
          class = CLS_BEG_CMT;
        else {
          ungetch(c);
          c = '/';
          class = CLS_OTHER;
        }
      } else
        class = CLS_OTHER;
      break;
    case '*':
      if (in_comment) {
        c = getch();
        if (c == '/')
          class = CLS_END_CMT;
        else {
          ungetch(c);
          class = CLS_OTHER;
        }
      } else
        class = CLS_OTHER;
      break;
    default:
      if (c == (-1))
        return 0;
      class = CLS_OTHER;
    }
    switch (class | in_comment) {
    case CLS_WS:
    case CLS_WS | CLS_IN_CMT:
    case CLS_OTHER | CLS_IN_CMT:
      break;
    case CLS_BEG_CMT:
      in_comment = CLS_IN_CMT;
      break;
    case CLS_OTHER:
      ungetch(c);
      return beg_line;
    case CLS_END_CMT | CLS_IN_CMT:
      in_comment = 0;
      break;
    case CLS_BEG_CMT | CLS_IN_CMT:
    case CLS_END_CMT:
    default:
      printf("can't happen\n");
      break;
    }
  }
}

test3
Prediction: int skipws_name_conflict(void) {
  int c;
  int state;

  while (1) {
    c = getch();
    switch (c) {
    case ' ':
    case '\t':
    case '\n':
    case '\r':
    case '\f':
    case '\v':
      state = 0;
      break;
    case '*':
      state = 3;
      break;
    case '/':
      c = getch();
      if (c == '*')
        state = 1;
      else {
        ungetch(c);
        state = 3;
      }
      break;
    case EOF:
      return 0;
    default:
      state = 3;
      break;
    }
    switch (state) {
    case 0:
      return 0;
    case 1:
      return 1;
    case 3:
      break;
    default:
      puts("can't happen");
      break;
    }
  }
}

Function: static int getstelem(char **wordp, int *limp, int quote) {
  int c;
  c = getch();
  if (c == quote || c == (-1))
    return 0;
  if (c != '\\') {
    putch(wordp, limp, c);
    return 1;
  }
  c = getch();
  if (c == (-1))
    return 0;
  {
    static const char escapes[] = {"''??\"\"\\\\a\ab\bf\fn\nr\rt\tv\v"};
    const char *cp = strchr(escapes, c);
    if (cp != ((void *)0)) {
      putch(wordp, limp, cp[1]);
      return 1;
    }
  }
  {
    unsigned char v = 0;
    if (c == 'x' || c == 'X')
      for (;;) {
        static const char hexits[] = "0123456789abcdef";
        const char *p;
        c = getch();
        p = strchr(hexits, tolower((unsigned char)c));
        if (p == ((void *)0))
          break;
        v = v * 16 + (p - hexits);
      }
    else {
      int i;
      for (i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
        v = v * 8 + (c - '0');
        c = getch();
        if (c < '0' || c > '7')
          break;
      }
    }
    putch(wordp, limp, v);
    ungetch(c);
  }
  return 1;
}

test3
Prediction: int getstelem_name_conflict(char *s, int *i, int delim) {
  static struct {
    char c;
    char r;
  } escapes[] = {
      {'n', '\n'},  {'r', '\r'},  {'t', '\t'},  {'v', '\v'},
      {'b', '\b'},  {'f', '\f'},  {'a', '\a'},  {'\\', '\\'},
      {'\'', '\''}, {'\"', '\"'}, {'\?', '\?'},
  };
  int c, j, k;

  c = getch();
  if (c == delim || c == -1)
    return 0;
  if (c == '\\') {
    c = getch();
    if (c == -1)
      return 0;
    for (j = 0; j < sizeof(escapes) / sizeof(escapes[0]); j++)
      if (escapes[j].c == c) {
        putch(s, i, escapes[j].r);
        return 1;
      }
    k = 0;
    if (c == 'x' || c == 'X') {
      while ((c = getch()) != -1 &&
             strchr("0123456789abcdef", tolower(c)) != NULL)
        k = k * 16 +
            (strchr("0123456789abcdef", tolower(c)) - "0123456789abcdef");
    } else {
      for (j = 0; j < 3; j++) {
        k = k * 8 + c - '0';
        c = getch();
        if (c < '0' || c > '7')
          break;
      }
    }
    putch(s, i, k);
    ungetch(c);
    return 1;
  }
  putch(s, i, c);
  return 1;
}

Function: long htoi(char s[]) {
  char *p = &s[strlen(s) - 1];
  long deci = 0, dig = 0;
  int pos = 0;
  while (p >= s) {
    if ((dig = hchartoi(*p, pos)) < 0) {
      printf("Error\n");
      return -1;
    }
    deci += dig;
    --p;
    ++pos;
  }
  return deci;
}

    p--;
    i++;
  }
  return n;
}

Function: long hchartoi(char hexdig, int pos) {
  char hexdigits[] = "0123456789ABCDEF";
  char *p = &hexdigits[0];
  long deci = 0;
  int i;
  while (*p != toupper(hexdig) && deci < 16) {
    ++p;
    ++deci;
  }
  if (*p == toupper(hexdig)) {
    for (i = 0; i < pos; i++)
      deci *= 16;
    return deci;
  }
  return -1;
}

test3
Prediction: long hchartoi_name_conflict(char c, int n) {
  char *hex = "0123456789ABCDEF";
  char *p = hex;
  long i = 0;
  int j;

  while (*p != toupper(c) && i < 16)
    p++, i++;

  if (*p != toupper(c))
    return -1;

  for (j = 0; j < n; j++)
    i <<= 4;

  return i;
}

Function: int any(char s1[], char s2[]) {
  int i;
  int j;
  int pos;
  pos = -1;
  for (i = 0; pos == -1 && s1[i] != '\x00'; i++) {
    for (j = 0; pos == -1 && s2[j] != '\x00'; j++) {
      if (s2[j] == s1[i]) {
        pos = i;
      }
    }
  }
  return pos;
}

        k = i;

C_COMPILE/the_c_programming_language_tiejianluo/Exercise/chapter2/20501.c
Function: int any(char *s1, char *s2) {
  char array[256];
  int i;
  if (s1 == ((void *)0)) {
    if (s2 == ((void *)0)) {
      return (0);
    } else {
      return (-1);
    }
  }
  for (i = 0; i < 256; i++) {
    array[i] = 0;
  }
  while (*s2 != '\x00') {
    array[*s2] = 1;
    s2++;
  }
  i = 0;
  while (s1[i] != '\x00') {
    if (array[s1[i]] == 1) {
      return (i);
    }
    i++;
  }
  return (-1);
}

test3
Prediction: int any_name_conflict(char *s1, char *s2) {
  int i, j;
  char c[256];

  if (s1 == NULL)
    return (s2 == NULL) ? 0 : -1;

  for (i = 0; i < 256; i++)
    c[i] = 0;

  for (i = 0; s2[i] != '\0'; i++)
    c[s2[i]] = 1;

  for (i = 0; s1[i] != '\0'; i++)
    if (c[s1[i]] == 1)
      return i;

  return -1;
}

C_COMPILE/the_c_programming_language_tiejianluo/Exercise/chapter2/20800.c
Function: unsigned int rightrot(unsigned int x, unsigned int n) {
  while (n > 0) {
    if ((x & 1) == 1)
      x = (x >> 1) | ~(~0U >> 1);
    else
      x = (x >> 1);
    n--;
  }
  return x;
}

test3
Prediction: unsigned rightrot_name_conflict(unsigned x, int n) {
  int i;
  for (i = n; i != 0; --i)
    if ((x & 01) == 0)
      x >>= 1;
    else
      x = (x >> 1) | (~(~0U >> 1));
  return x;
}

Function: int hexalpha_to_int(int c) {
  char hexalpha[] = "aAbBcCdDeEfF";
  int i;
  int answer = 0;
  for (i = 0; answer == 0 && hexalpha[i] != '\x00'; i++) {
    if (hexalpha[i] == c) {
      answer = 10 + (i / 2);
    }
  }
  return answer;
}

Function: unsigned int htoi(const char s[]) {
  unsigned int answer = 0;
  int i = 0;
  int valid = 1;
  int hexit;
  if (s[i] == '0') {
    ++i;
    if (s[i] == 'x' || s[i] == 'X') {
      ++i;
    }
  }
  while (valid && s[i] != '\x00') {
    answer = answer * 16;
    if (s[i] >= '0' && s[i] <= '9') {
      answer = answer + (s[i] - '0');
    } else {
      hexit = hexalpha_to_int(s[i]);
      if (hexit == 0) {
        valid = 0;
      } else {
        answer = answer + hexit;
      }
    }
    ++i;
  }
  if (!valid) {
    answer = 0;
  }
  return answer;
}

test3
Prediction: int htoi_name_conflict(char s[]) {
  int i, n, inword, hexdigit;

  i = 0;
  if (s[i] == '0') {
    ++i;
    if (s[i] == 'x' || s[i] == 'X')
      ++i;
  }
  n = 0;
  inword = 1;
  for (; inword && (s[i] != '\0'); ++i) {
    n = n * 16;
    if (s[i] >= '0' && s[i] <= '9')
      n = n + s[i] - '0';
    else if ((hexdigit = hexalpha_to_int(s[i])) != 0)
      n = n + hexdigit;
    else
      inword = 0;
  }
  if (!inword)
    n = 0;
  return n;
}

Function: int readbuff(char *buffer) {
  size_t i = 0;
  int c;
  while (i < 81) {
    c = getchar();
    if (c == (-1))
      return -1;
    if (c == '\n')
      return 0;
    buffer[i++] = c;
  }
  return 1;
}

Function: int copyline(char *buffer) {
  size_t i;
  int c;
  int status = 1;
  for (i = 0; i < 81; i++)
    putchar(buffer[i]);
  while (status == 1) {
    c = getchar();
    if (c == (-1))
      status = -1;
    else if (c == '\n')
      status = 0;
    else
      putchar(c);
  }
  putchar('\n');
  return status;
}

C_COMPILE/the_c_programming_language_tiejianluo/Exercise/chapter1/12311.c
Function: int options(const char *afterdash, char **moreargs) {
  int nmore = 0, c;
  while ((c = *afterdash++) != '\x00') {
    if (c == 'o') {
      if (*afterdash) {
        outname = afterdash;
        afterdash = "";
      } else if (moreargs[nmore] != ((void *)0))
        outname = moreargs[nmore++];
      else
        usage();
    } else if (c == 't')
      trigraphs = 0;
    else if (c == 'w')
      whitespace = 0;
    else if (c == '9')
      c99 = 1;
    else
      usage();
  }
  return nmore;
}

test3
Prediction: int options_name_conflict(char *arg, char **argv) {
  int i;

  i = 0;
  while (*arg) {
    switch (*arg++) {
    case 'o':
      if (*arg) {
        arg = "";
        outname = arg;
        break;
      }
      if (argv[i]) {
        outname = argv[i];
        i++;
        break;
      }
      usage();

    case 't':
      trigraphs = 0;
      break;

    case 'w':
      whitespace = 0;
      break;

    case '9':
      c99 = 1;
      break;

    default:
      usage();
    }
  }
  return i;
}

Function: int day_of_year(int year, int month, int day) {
  int i, leap;
  leap = (year % 4 == 0 && year % 100 != 0) || year % 400 == 0;
  for (i = 1; i < month; i++)
    day += daytab[leap][i];
  return day;
}

test3
Prediction: int day_of_year_name_conflict(int year, int month, int day) {
  int i, leap;

  leap = (year % 4 == 0 && year % 100 != 0) || year % 400 == 0;
  for (i = 1; i < month; i++)
    day += daytab[leap][i];
  return day;
}

Function: int day_of_year_pointer(int year, int month, int day) {
  int i, leap;
  char *p;
  leap = (year % 4 == 0 && year % 100 != 0) || year % 400 == 0;
  p = &daytab[leap][1];
  for (i = 1; i < month; i++) {
    day += *p;
    ++p;
  }
  return day;
}

test3
Prediction: int day_of_year_pointer_name_conflict(int year, int month, int day) {
  int i, leap;
  char *p;

  leap = (year % 4 == 0 && year % 100 != 0) || year % 400 == 0;
  p = &daytab[leap][1];
  for (i = 1; i < month; i++)
    day += *p++;
  return day;
}

Function: int getint(int *pn) {
  int c, sign;
  while (((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c = getch()))] & (unsigned short)_ISspace))
    ;
  if (!((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c))] & (unsigned short)_ISdigit) &&
      c != (-1) && c != '+' && c != '-') {
    ungetch(c);
    return 0;
  }
  sign = (c == '-') ? -1 : 1;
  if (c == '+' || c == '-')
    c = getch();
  for (*pn = 0; ((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c))] & (unsigned short)_ISdigit);
       c = getch())
    *pn = 10 * *pn + (c - '0');
  *pn *= sign;
  if (c != (-1))
    ungetch(c);
  return c;
}

test3
Prediction: int getint_name_conflict(int *pn) {
  int c, sign;

  while (isspace(c = getch()))
    ;

  if (!isdigit(c) && c != EOF && c != '+' && c != '-') {
    ungetch(c);
    return 0;
  }

  sign = (c == '-') ? -1 : 1;

  if (c == '+' || c == '-')
    c = getch();

  for (*pn = 0; isdigit(c); c = getch())
    *pn = 10 * *pn + (c - '0');

  *pn *= sign;

  if (c != EOF)
    ungetch(c);

  return c;
}

Function: int strend(char *s, char *t) {
  int Result = 0;
  int s_length = 0;
  int t_length = 0;
  s_length = strlen(s);
  t_length = strlen(t);
  if (t_length <= s_length) {
    s += s_length - t_length;
    if (0 == strcmp(s, t)) {
      Result = 1;
    }
  }
  return Result;
}

    if (!strcmp(s + slen - tlen, t))
      ret = 1;
  }

  return ret;
}

Function: char *liw_strncpy(char *s, const char *ct, size_t n) {
  char *p;
  p = s;
  for (; n > 0 && *ct != '\x00'; --n)
    *p++ = *ct++;
  for (; n > 0; --n)
    *p++ = '\x00';
  return s;
}

    *d = *s;
    d++;
    s++;
    n--;
  }

  while (n) {
    *d = '\0';
    d++;
    n--;
  }

  return dest;
}

Function: char *liw_strncat(char *s, const char *ct, size_t n) {
  char *p;
  p = s;
  while (*p != '\x00')
    ++p;
  for (; n > 0 && *ct != '\x00'; --n)
    *p++ = *ct++;
  *p = '\x00';
  return s;
}

    *dest++ = *src++;
  *dest = '\0';
  return ret;

Function: int liw_strncmp(const char *cs, const char *ct, size_t n) {
  while (n > 0 && *cs == *ct && *cs != '\x00') {
    ++cs;
    ++ct;
    --n;
  }
  if (n == 0 || *cs == *ct)
    return 0;
  if (*(unsigned char *)cs < *(unsigned char *)ct)
    return -1;
  return 1;
}

test3
Prediction: int liw_strncmp_name_conflict(const char *s1, const char *s2, size_t n) {
  while (n && *s1 == *s2 && *s1) {
    s1++;
    s2++;
    n--;
  }

  if (n == 0 || *s1 == *s2)
    return 0;

  if (*s1 < *s2)
    return -1;

  return 1;
}

Function: int day_of_year(int year, int month, int day) {
  int i, leap;
  if (year < 1752 || month < 1 || month > 12 || day < 1)
    return -1;
  leap = (year % 4 == 0 && year % 100 != 0) || year % 400 == 0;
  if (day > daytab[leap][month])
    return -1;
  for (i = 1; i < month; i++)
    day += daytab[leap][i];
  return day;
}

test3

Function: int month_day(int year, int yearday, int *pmonth, int *pday) {
  int i, leap;
  if (year < 1752 || yearday < 1)
    return -1;
  leap = (year % 4 == 0 && year % 100 != 0) || year % 400 == 0;
  if ((leap && yearday > 366) || (!leap && yearday > 365))
    return -1;
  for (i = 1; yearday > daytab[leap][i]; i++)
    yearday -= daytab[leap][i];
  *pmonth = i;
  *pday = yearday;
  return 0;
}

test3
Prediction: int month_day_name_conflict(int year, int yearday, int *pmonth, int *pday) {
  int i, leap;

  if (year < 1752 || yearday < 1)
    return -1;

  leap = (year % 4 == 0 && year % 100 != 0) || year % 400 == 0;
  if (leap && yearday > 365)
    return -1;
  if (!leap && yearday > 366)
    return -1;

  for (i = 1; yearday > daytab[leap][i]; i++)
    yearday -= daytab[leap][i];
  *pmonth = i;
  *pday = yearday;
  return 0;
}

Function: struct Node *buildBST(int a[], int start, int end) {
  if (start <= end) {
    int mid = (start + end) / 2;
    struct Node *root = (struct Node *)malloc(sizeof(struct Node));
    root->val = a[mid];
    root->left = buildBST(a, start, mid - 1);
    root->right = buildBST(a, mid + 1, end);
    return root;
  }
  return ((void *)0);
}

  if (start > end)
    return NULL;

  int mid = (start + end) / 2;
  struct node *root = (struct node *)malloc(sizeof(struct node));
  root->data = arr[mid];
  root->left = buildBST_name_conflict(arr, start, mid - 1);
  root->right = buildBST_name_conflict(arr, mid + 1, end);

  return root;
}

Function: int isBSTUtil(struct Node *node, int min, int max) {
  if (node == ((void *)0))
    return 1;
  if (node->val < min || node->val > max)
    return 0;
  int leftIsBST = isBSTUtil(node->left, min, node->val - 1);
  int rightIsBST = isBSTUtil(node->right, node->val + 1, max);
  return leftIsBST && rightIsBST;
}

Function: struct node *reverse(struct node *list) {
  struct node *prev = 0;
  struct node *current = list;
  while (current != 0) {
    struct node *saved_next_link = current->next;
    current->next = prev;
    prev = current;
    current = saved_next_link;
  }
  return current;
}

test3
Prediction: struct node *reverse_name_conflict(struct node *head) {
  struct node *prev = NULL;
  struct node *curr = head;
  struct node *next = NULL;

  while (curr != NULL) {
    next = curr->next;
    curr->next = prev;
    prev = curr;
    curr = next;
  }

  return prev;
}

C_COMPILE/C-Programming_jigarshah-platsec/TREE_BinarySearch.c
Function: int binarySearch(int arr[], int low, int high, int val) {
  if (low <= high) {
    int mid = (low + high) >> 1;
    if (arr[mid] == val)
      return mid;
    if (arr[mid] > val)
      binarySearch(arr, 0, mid - 1, val);
    else
      binarySearch(arr, mid + 1, high, val);
  }
  return -1;
}

test3
Prediction: int binarySearch_name_conflict(int *arr, int low, int high, int key) {
  if (high < low)
    return -1;

  int mid = low + (high - low) / 2;
  if (arr[mid] == key)
    return mid;

  if (arr[mid] > key)
    return binarySearch_name_conflict(arr, low, mid - 1, key);
  else
    return binarySearch_name_conflict(arr, mid + 1, high, key);
}

C_COMPILE/C-Programming_jigarshah-platsec/GENERAL_atoi.c
Function: int hisatoi(char *pointer) {
  int mul = 1;
  int result = 0;
  char *current = pointer;
  while (*current != '\x00') {
    if (*current >= '0' && *current <= '9')
      mul = mul * 10;
    current++;
  }
  mul = mul / 10;
  current = pointer;
  while (*pointer != '\x00') {
    result = result + ((*pointer % 48) * mul);
    mul = mul / 10;
    pointer++;
  }
  return result;
}

test3
Prediction: int hisatoi_name_conflict(char *str) {
  int i, n;
  char *p;

  n = 0;
  for (p = str; *p != '\0'; p++)
    if (*p >= '0' && *p <= '9')
      i *= 10;
  for (p = str; *p != '\0'; p++) {
    n += (*p - '0') * i;
    i /= 10;
  }
  return n;
}

Function: int myatoi(char *str) {
  int value;
  char *current = str;
  while (((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((*current))] & (unsigned short)_ISdigit)) {
    value = value * 10;
    value = value + (*current - '0');
    current++;
  }
  return value;
}

test3
Prediction: int myatoi_name_conflict(char *str) {
  int num = 0;
  while (__ctype_b_loc().n[*str] & 0x800)
    num = num * 10 + *str++ - '0';
  return num;
}

C_COMPILE/C-Programming_jigarshah-platsec/BIT_duplicateNumber.c
Function: int getSingle(int a[], int n) {
  int num = a[0];
  int result = 0;
  for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
    result = num ^ a[i];
    num = a[i];
  }
  return result;
}

test3
Prediction: int getSingle_name_conflict(int *nums, int numsSize) {
  int i, res = 0, tmp;
  for (i = 1; i < numsSize; i++) {
    tmp = res;
    res = res ^ nums[i];
    nums[i] = tmp;
  }
  return res;
}

Function: char *reverse_string(char *str, int strlen) {
  char temp = '\x00';
  int i = 0;
  int j = 0;
  for (i = 0, j = strlen - 1; i < strlen / 2; i++, j--) {
    temp = str[i];
    str[i] = str[j];
    str[j] = temp;
  }
  return str;
}

Function: int is_supp_ref(s1)
char *s1;
{
  int i, x;
  if (strlen(s1) < 6)
    return (0);
  if (!(s1[0] == '*' && s1[1] == '*'))
    return (0);
  i = 2;
  while (((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((s1[i]))] & (unsigned short)_ISdigit))
    i++;
  if (i == 2 || s1[i] != ';')
    return (0);
  i++;
  x = i;
  while (((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((s1[i]))] & (unsigned short)_ISdigit))
    i++;
  if (i == x || s1[i] != ';')
    return (0);
  return (1);
}

Function: int RegExpCompile(char *source) {
  register char *s;
  register char *lp;
  register int c;
  int o;
  char *spp;
  s = source;
  lp = pp = pbuf;
  while (c = *s++) {
    if (c == 20) {
      lp = pp;
      if (!store(4))
        return (0);
      if (!store(15))
        return (0);
      if (!store(15))
        return (0);
      spp = pp;
      while (--pp > lp)
        *pp = pp[-1];
      *pp = 7;
      pp = spp;
      continue;
    }
    if (c == 7 || c == 8) {
      if (pp == pbuf || (o = pp[-1]) == 2 || o == 3 || o == 7 || o == 8 ||
          o == 9)
        return (0);
      if (!store(15))
        return (0);
      if (!store(15))
        return (0);
      spp = pp;
      while (--pp > lp)
        *pp = pp[-1];
      *pp = c;
      pp = spp;
      continue;
    }
    lp = pp;
    switch (c) {
    case '^':
      if (!store(2))
        return (0);
      break;
    case 3:
      if (!store(3))
        return (0);
      break;
    case 4:
      if (!store(4))
        return (0);
      break;
    case 16:
      if (!(s = cclass(source, s)))
        return (0);
      break;
    case 19:
      if (*s)
        c = *s++;
    default:
      if (!store(1))
        return (0);
      if (!store(tolower(c)))
        return (0);
    }
  }
  if (!store(15))
    return (0);
  if (!store(0))
    return (0);
  return (1);
}

Function: int RegExpStrip(char *ss) {
  char *s = ss;
  while (*s) {
    if (*s == 19) {
      strdelete(s, 1);
    } else if (*s == 7) {
      if (s != ss)
        *(s - 1) = '\x00';
      else
        *s = '\x00';
      return (1);
    } else {
      if (*s == 4 || *s == 3 || *s == 17 || *s == 16 || *s == 8 || *s == 20) {
        *s = '\x00';
        return (1);
      }
    }
    s++;
  }
  return (1);
}

Function: int IsRegExp(char *s) {

    if (*s == '\\')
      s++;
    else {
      if (*s == '?' || *s == '[' || *s == ']' || *s == '*' || *s == '+' ||
          *s == '@')
        return (1);
    }
    s++;
  }
  return (0);
}

Function: static char *cclass(char *source, char *src) {

  o = 5;
  if (*s == 18) {
    ++s;
    o = 6;
  }
  if (!store(o))
    return (((void *)0));
  cp = pp;
  if (!store(0))
    return (((void *)0));
  while ((c = *s++) && c != 17) {
    if (c == 19) {
      if ((c = *s++) == '\x00')
        return (((void *)0));
      else {
        if (!store(tolower(c)))
          return (((void *)0));
      }
    } else if (c == '-' && (pp - cp) > 1 && *s != 17 && *s != '\x00') {
      c = pp[-1];
      pp[-1] = 14;
      if (!store(c))
        return (((void *)0));
      c = *s++;
      if (!store(tolower(c)))
        return (((void *)0));
    } else {
      if (!store(tolower(c)))
        return (((void *)0));
    }
  }

    return (((void *)0));
  if ((c = (pp - cp)) >= 256)
    return (((void *)0));
  if (c == 0)
    return (((void *)0));
  *cp = c;
  return (s);
}

    p++;
    c = 6;
  }

    return NULL;
  if (!store('\0'))
    return NULL;
  start = pp;
  while ((c = *p++) != '\0' && c != '\x11') {
    if (c == '\x13') {
      if (*p == '\0')
        return NULL;
      if (!store(tolower(*p++)))
        return NULL;
      continue;
    }
    if (c == '-' && pp - start > 1 && *p != '\x11' && *p != '\0') {
      c = *--pp;
      *pp = '\x0e';
      if (!store(c))
        return NULL;
      if (!store(tolower(*p++)))
        return NULL;
      continue;
    }
    if (!store(tolower(c)))
      return NULL;
  }
  if (c != '\x11')
    return NULL;
  len = pp - start;
  if (len > 255 || len == 0)
    return NULL;
  *start = len;
  return p;
}

Function: static char *pmatch(char *line, char *pattern) {
  register char *l;
  register char *p;
  register char c;
  char *e;
  int op;
  int n;
  char *are;
  l = line;
  p = pattern;
  while ((op = *p++) != 15) {
    switch (op) {
    case 1:
      if (tolower(*l) != *p++)
        return (0);
      l++;
      break;
    case 2:
      if (l != lbuf)
        return (0);
      break;
    case 3:
      if (*l != '\x00')
        return (0);
      break;
    case 4:
      if (*l++ == '\x00')
        return (0);
      break;
    case 11:
      if ((c = *l++) < '0' || (c > '9'))
        return (0);
      break;
    case 10:
      c = tolower(*l);
      l++;
      if (c < 'a' || c > 'z')
        return (0);
      break;
    case 12:
      c = tolower(*l);
      l++;
      if (c >= 'a' && c <= 'z')
        break;
      else if (c < '0' || c > '9')
        return (0);
      break;
    case 13:
      c = *l++;
      if (c == 0 || c > ' ')
        return (0);
      break;
    case 5:
    case 6:
      c = tolower(*l);
      l++;
      n = *p++ & 255;
      do {
        if (*p == 14) {
          p += 3;
          n -= 2;
          if (c >= p[-2] && c <= p[-1])
            break;
        } else if (c == *p++)
          break;
      } while (--n > 1);
      if ((op == 5) == (n <= 1))
        return (0);
      if (op == 5)
        p += n - 2;
      break;
    case 9:
      e = pmatch(l, p);
      while (*p++ != 15)
        ;
      if (e)
        l = e;
      break;
    case 8:
      if ((l = pmatch(l, p)) == 0)
        return (0);
    case 7:
      are = l;
      while (*l && (e = pmatch(l, p)))
        l = e;
      while (*p++ != 15)
        ;
      while (l >= are) {
        if (e = pmatch(l, p))
          return (e);
        --l;
      }
      return (0);
    default:
      return (0);
    }
  }
  return (l);
}

        return NULL;
      s++;
      break;
    case 2:

        return NULL;
      break;

        return NULL;
      break;

        return NULL;
      break;
    case 5:
    case 6:

            goto found;
          p++;
          break;
        default:
          if (c1 == *p++)
            goto found;
          break;
        }

        ;

      if (c < 'a' || c > 'z')
        return NULL;
      s++;

Function: int read_map(mapfn)
char *mapfn;
{
  FILE *mfp;
  int count = 0, pos, pos2;
  char line[300];
  if ((mfp = fopen(mapfn, "r")) == ((void *)0)) {
    rep_err("Mapping file not found.");
  }
  fgets(line, 300, mfp);
  pos = 0;
  pos2 = 0;
  while (line[pos] != '\t' && line[pos] != '\n') {
    mapping[count].from[pos] = line[pos];
    pos++;
  }
  mapping[count].from[pos] = '\x00';
  pos++;
  while (line[pos] != '\n' && line[pos] != '\x00') {
    mapping[count].to[pos2] = line[pos];
    pos++;
    pos2++;
  }
  mapping[count].to[pos2] = '\x00';
  while (!feof(mfp)) {
    count++;
    fgets(line, 300, mfp);
    pos = 0;
    pos2 = 0;
    while (line[pos] != '\t' && line[pos] != '\n') {
      mapping[count].from[pos] = line[pos];
      pos++;
    }
    mapping[count].from[pos] = '\x00';
    pos++;
    while (line[pos] != '\n' && line[pos] != '\x00') {
      mapping[count].to[pos2] = line[pos];
      pos++;
      pos2++;
    }
    mapping[count].to[pos2] = '\x00';
  }
  printf("%d entries found in mapping file.\n", count);
  return (count - 1);
}

Function: linkent *semtag_strip_marker(s1, idcn, idno, idpo, slash_prefer_first,
                             strip_gender_marker)
char *s1;
int *idcn;
int *idno;
int *idpo;
int slash_prefer_first;
int strip_gender_marker;
{
  int x, smln, endpt, templn = -1;
  char temp[300];
  linkent *new, *end, *link;
  link = ((void *)0);
  end = link;
  *idcn = *idno = *idpo = 0;
  endpt = smln = strlen(s1);
  for (x = 0; x <= smln; x++) {
    if (s1[x] == '[') {
      if (x < endpt)
        endpt = x;
      x++;
      if (s1[x] == 'i') {
        templn = -1;
        temp[++templn] = s1[++x];
        while (temp[templn] != '.')
          temp[++templn] = s1[++x];
        temp[templn] = '\x00';
        *idcn = atoi(temp);
        templn = -1;
        temp[++templn] = s1[++x];
        while (temp[templn] != '.')
          temp[++templn] = s1[++x];
        temp[templn] = '\x00';
        *idno = atoi(temp);
        templn = -1;
        temp[++templn] = s1[++x];
        while ((temp[templn] != '\x00') && (temp[templn] != '['))
          temp[++templn] = s1[++x];
        temp[templn] = '\x00';
        *idpo = atoi(temp);
        x--;
      } else if (strchr("mashd", s1[x])) {
        templn = -1;
        new = (linkent *)myalloc(sizeof(linkent));
        new->linktype = s1[x];
        temp[++templn] = s1[++x];
        while (temp[templn] != '.')
          temp[++templn] = s1[++x];
        temp[templn] = '\x00';
        new->linkcn = atoi(temp);
        templn = -1;
        temp[++templn] = s1[++x];
        while (temp[templn] != '.')
          temp[++templn] = s1[++x];
        temp[templn] = '\x00';
        new->linkno = atoi(temp);
        templn = -1;
        temp[++templn] = s1[++x];
        while ((temp[templn] != '\x00') && (temp[templn] != '['))
          temp[++templn] = s1[++x];
        temp[templn] = '\x00';
        new->linkpo = atoi(temp);
        new->next = ((void *)0);
        if (link == ((void *)0)) {
          link = new;
          end = link;
        } else {
          end->next = new;
          end = end->next;
        }
        x--;
      }
    } else if (((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((s1[x]))] &
                (unsigned short)_ISlower) &&
               strip_gender_marker) {
      if (x < endpt)
        endpt = x;
    } else if (slash_prefer_first && s1[x] == '/') {
      if (x < endpt)
        endpt = x;
    } else if (s1[x] == '{') {
      if (x < endpt)
        endpt = x;
    }
  }
  s1[endpt] = '\x00';
  return (link);
}

Function: int power(int m, int n) {
  int i, p;
  p = 1;
  for (i = 1; i <= n; i++)
    p *= m;
  return p;
}

Function: int *twoSum_heapSort(int *nums, int numsSize, int target) {
  int *result;
  int i, j, s;
  Element *A;
  result = (int *)malloc(sizeof(int) * 2);
  A = (Element *)malloc(sizeof(Element) * numsSize);
  for (i = 0; i < numsSize; i++) {
    A[i].pos = i;
    A[i].value = nums[i];
  }
  heapSort(A, numsSize);
  i = 0;
  j = numsSize - 1;
  while (1) {
    s = A[i].value + A[j].value;
    if (s == target) {
      result[0] = A[i].pos;
      result[1] = A[j].pos;
      break;
    } else if (s > target) {
      j--;
    } else {
      i++;
    }
  }
  return result;
}

test3

  struct HeapNode *heap =
      (struct HeapNode *)malloc(sizeof(struct HeapNode) * numsSize);
  for (int i = 0; i < numsSize; i++) {
    heap[i].index = i;
    heap[i].val = nums[i];
  }
  heapSort(heap, numsSize);
  int i = 0, j = numsSize - 1;
  while (heap[i].val + heap[j].val != target) {
    if (heap[i].val + heap[j].val > target) {
      j--;
    } else {
      i++;
    }
  }
  result[0] = heap[i].index;
  result[1] = heap[j].index;
  return result;
}

Function: int *twoSum(int *nums, int numsSize, int target) {
  int *result;
  register int i, j, s;
  register list **pList;
  result = (int *)malloc(sizeof(int) * 2);
  pList = (list **)malloc(sizeof(list *) * numsSize);
  for (i = 0; i < numsSize; i++) {
    pList[i] = (list *)malloc(sizeof(list));
    pList[i]->value = nums[i];
    pList[i]->pos = i;
    pList[i]->next = ((void *)0);
  }
  mergeSort(pList, numsSize);
  i = 0;
  j = numsSize - 1;
  while (1) {
    s = pList[i]->value + pList[j]->value;
    if (s == target) {
      if (pList[i]->pos <= pList[j]->pos) {
        result[0] = pList[i]->pos;
        result[1] = pList[j]->pos;
      } else {
        result[0] = pList[j]->pos;
        result[1] = pList[i]->pos;
      }
      break;
    } else if (s > target) {
      j--;
    } else {
      i++;
    }
  }
  return result;
}

C_COMPILE/f1x_msv-lab/demo/sort.c
Function: int Partition(int a[], int p, int r) {
  int x = a[r];
  int i = p - 1;
  int temp = 0;
  for (int j = p; j < r - 1; j++) {
    if (a[j] <= x) {
      i++;
      temp = a[i];
      a[i] = a[j];
      a[j] = temp;
    }
  }
  temp = a[i + 1];
  a[i + 1] = a[r];
  a[r] = temp;
  return (i + 1);
}

test3

    if (A[j] <= x) {
      i++;
      temp = A[i];
      A[i] = A[j];
      A[j] = temp;
    }
  }
  temp = A[i + 1];
  A[i + 1] = A[r];
  A[r] = temp;
  return i + 1;
}

Function: const char *get_the_good_string(Corde corde, Accord accord) {

  case THIRD:

  case FOURTH:

  case FIFTH:

  default:

}

Function: char get_the_good_fret(Note note, Corde corde) {
  switch (corde) {
  case THIRD:
    return array_frette[((note + 9) % 12)];
  case FOURTH:
    return array_frette[((note + 2) % 12)];
  case FIFTH:
    return array_frette[((note + 7) % 12)];
  case SIXTH:

  default:
    return 0;
  }
}

Function: int addRecord(struct record **startptr, int uaccountno, char uname[],
              char uaddr[], int uyob) {
  struct record *newRecord = ((void *)0);
  int found = -2;
  newRecord = malloc(sizeof(struct record));
  if (debugmode == 1) {
    puts("");
    puts("**DEBUG**");
    puts("Function name: addRecord");
    printf("Parameters: startptr = %u, uaccountno = %i, ", startptr,
           uaccountno);
    printf("uname = %s, uaddr = %s, uyob = %i", uname, uaddr, uyob);
    puts("");
    puts("");
  }
  (*newRecord).accountno = uaccountno;
  strncpy((*newRecord).name, uname, 25);
  strncpy((*newRecord).address, uaddr, 80);
  (*newRecord).yearofbirth = uyob;
  (*newRecord).next = ((void *)0);
  if (*startptr == ((void *)0)) {
    *startptr = newRecord;
    found = 0;
  } else if ((*startptr) != ((void *)0)) {
    struct record *currentRecord;
    currentRecord = *startptr;
    found = -2;
    if ((*newRecord).accountno <= (**startptr).accountno) {
      (*newRecord).next = *startptr;
      *startptr = newRecord;
      found = 0;
    }
    while ((*currentRecord).next != ((void *)0) && found != 0) {
      if ((*newRecord).accountno <= (*((*currentRecord).next)).accountno) {
        (*newRecord).next = (*currentRecord).next;
        (*currentRecord).next = newRecord;
        found = 0;
      }
      if ((*newRecord).accountno > (*((*currentRecord).next)).accountno) {
        currentRecord = (*currentRecord).next;
      }
    }
    if (found == -2) {
      (*currentRecord).next = newRecord;
      found = 0;
    }
  }
  return found;
}

    puts("");
    puts("**DEBUG**");
    puts("Function name: modifyRecord");

    printf("input = %s", input);
    puts("");
    puts("");

    struct record *currentRecord;
    currentRecord = start;
    if ((*start).accountno == uaccountno) {
      while (currentRecord != ((void *)0) && done != 1) {
        if ((*currentRecord).accountno == uaccountno) {
          strncpy((*currentRecord).address, input, 80);
          currentRecord = (*currentRecord).next;
          found = found + 1;
        } else {
          done = 1;
        }
      }
    } else {
      if ((*currentRecord).next != ((void *)0)) {
        currentRecord = (*currentRecord).next;
        while (currentRecord != ((void *)0)) {

Function: int printRecord(struct record *start, int uaccountno) {

  int done = 0;
  if (debugmode == 1) {
    puts("");
    puts("**DEBUG**");

    puts("");
    puts("");
  }

    currentRecord = start;

          fprintf(stdout, "%i\n", (*currentRecord).yearofbirth);

          found = found + 1;

          done = 1;
        }
      }

        currentRecord = (*currentRecord).next;
        while (currentRecord != ((void *)0)) {

            fprintf(stdout, "%i\n", (*currentRecord).accountno);
            fprintf(stdout, "%s\n", (*currentRecord).name);
            fprintf(stdout, "%s\n", (*currentRecord).address);
            fprintf(stdout, "%i\n", (*currentRecord).yearofbirth);

        }

  }

Function: int deleteRecord(struct record **startptr, int uaccountno) {
  int found = 0;
  int done = 0;
  if (debugmode == 1) {
    puts("");
    puts("**DEBUG**");
    puts("Function name: deleteRecord");
    printf("Parameters: startptr = %u, uaccountno = %i, ", startptr,
           uaccountno);
    puts("");
    puts("");
  }
  if (*startptr != ((void *)0)) {
    if ((**startptr).accountno == uaccountno) {
      while (*startptr != ((void *)0) && done != 1) {
        if ((**startptr).accountno == uaccountno) {
          struct record *tempRecord;
          tempRecord = *startptr;
          *startptr = (**startptr).next;
          (*tempRecord).next = ((void *)0);
          free(tempRecord);
          found = found + 1;
        } else {
          done = 1;
        }
      }
    } else {
      if ((**startptr).next != ((void *)0)) {
        struct record *previous = *startptr;
        struct record *current = (**startptr).next;
        while (current != ((void *)0)) {
          if ((*current).accountno == uaccountno) {
            struct record *temp;
            (*previous).next = (*current).next;
            (*current).next = ((void *)0);
            temp = current;
            current = (*previous).next;
            free(temp);
            found = found + 1;
          } else if ((*current).accountno != uaccountno) {
            current = (*current).next;
            previous = (*previous).next;
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
  return found;
}

  int found = 0;
  struct record *temp;
  struct record *temp2;

  if (debugmode == 1) {
    printf("\n");
    printf("**DEBUG**\n");
    printf("Function name: deleteRecord_name_conflict\n");
    printf("Parameters: startptr = %u, uaccountno = %i, ", startptr,
           uaccountno);
    printf("\n\n");
  }

  if (*startptr != NULL) {
    if (uaccountno == (*startptr)->accountno) {
      while (*startptr != NULL && found == 0) {
        if (uaccountno == (*startptr)->accountno) {
          temp = *startptr;
          *startptr = (*startptr)->next;
          temp->next = NULL;
          free(temp);
          count++;
        } else {
          found = 1;
        }
      }
    } else if ((*startptr)->next != NULL) {
      temp = *startptr;
      temp2 = (*startptr)->next;
      while (temp2 != NULL) {
        if (uaccountno == temp2->accountno) {
          temp->next = temp2->next;
          temp2->next = NULL;
          temp = temp->next;
          free(temp2);
          count++;
          temp2 = temp->next;
        } else if (uaccountno != temp2->accountno) {
          temp2 = temp2->next;
          temp = temp->next;
        }
      }
    }
  }
  return count;
}

Function: int readfile(struct record **linkedList, char filename[]) {
  char file[100] = "\000";
  char line[100] = "\000";
  char empty[2] = "";
  FILE *infilebuffer;
  int status;
  int accountno;
  char name[25];
  char address[80];
  int yearofbirth;
  char tempString[2] = "\000";
  int c = 0;
  if (debugmode == 1) {
    puts("");
    puts("**DEBUG**");
    puts("Function name: readfile");
    printf("Parameters: linkedList = %u, filename = %s, ", linkedList,
           filename);
    puts("");
    puts("");
  }
  strncpy(file, filename, 99);
  infilebuffer = fopen(file, "r");
  if (infilebuffer != ((void *)0)) {
    while (!feof(infilebuffer)) {
      strncpy(line, empty, 10);
      fgets(line, 9, infilebuffer);
      if (!feof(infilebuffer)) {
        removeTrailingSpace(line);
        accountno = atoi(line);
        strncpy(line, empty, 10);
        fgets(line, 99, infilebuffer);
        removeTrailingSpace(line);
        strncpy(name, line, (25 - 1));
        strncpy(line, empty, 10);
        while ((c != 94)) {
          c = fgetc(infilebuffer);
          if (c != 94) {
            tempString[0] = (char)c;
            strcat(line, tempString);
          }
        }
        strncpy(address, line, (80 - 1));
        while ((c != 10)) {
          c = fgetc(infilebuffer);
        }
        strncpy(line, empty, 10);
        fgets(line, 99, infilebuffer);
        removeTrailingSpace(line);
        yearofbirth = atoi(line);
        addRecord(linkedList, accountno, name, address, yearofbirth);
      }
    }
    status = 0;
    fclose(infilebuffer);
  } else {
    status = -1;
  }
  return (status);
}

Function: int is_strings_equals(char *a, char *b) {
  int i = 0;
  while ((a[i] == b[i]) && (a[i] != '\x00')) {
    i += 1;
  }
  return (a[i] == b[i]);
}

Function: static int wait_for_child() {
  int exit_read = 0;
  char exit_value = 0;
  int wait_status;
  while (1) {
    struct timeval tv;
    fd_set rfds;
    do {
      unsigned int __i;
      fd_set *__arr = (&rfds);
      for (__i = 0; __i < sizeof(fd_set) / sizeof(__fd_mask); ++__i)
        ((__arr)->fds_bits)[__i] = 0;
    } while (0);
    tv.tv_sec = 1;
    tv.tv_usec = 0;
    ((void)(((&rfds)
                 ->fds_bits)[((exit_pipe[0]) / (8 * (int)sizeof(__fd_mask)))] |=
            ((__fd_mask)(1UL
                         << ((exit_pipe[0]) % (8 * (int)sizeof(__fd_mask)))))));
    if (select(exit_pipe[0] + 1, &rfds, ((void *)0), ((void *)0), &tv) < 0)
      fatal("select: %s", strerror((*__errno_location())));
    if (waitpid(daemon_pid, &wait_status, 1) > 0)
      fatal("daemon shut down unexpectedly");
    if (((((&rfds)->fds_bits)[((exit_pipe[0]) / (8 * (int)sizeof(__fd_mask)))] &
          ((__fd_mask)(1UL << ((exit_pipe[0]) %
                               (8 * (int)sizeof(__fd_mask)))))) != 0))
      break;
  }
  exit_read = read(exit_pipe[0], &exit_value, 1);
  if (exit_read < 0)
    fatal("read: %s", strerror((*__errno_location())));
  return exit_value;
}

Prediction: int wait_for_child_name_conflict(void) {
  int ret = 0;
  char c = 0;

  do {
    fd_set fds;
    struct timeval tv;
    int status;

    for (unsigned int i = 0; i < sizeof(fds.fds_bits); i++)
      fds.fds_bits[i] = 0;

    tv.tv_sec = 1;
    tv.tv_usec = 0;

    fds.fds_bits[exit_pipe / (8 * sizeof(long))] |=
        (1UL << (exit_pipe % (8 * sizeof(long))));

    if (select(exit_pipe + 1, &fds, NULL, NULL, &tv) < 0)
      fatal("select: %s", strerror(*__errno_location()));

    if (waitpid(daemon_pid, &status, 1) > 0)
      fatal("daemon shut down unexpectedly");
  } while (!(fds.fds_bits[exit_pipe / (8 * sizeof(long))] &
             (1UL << (exit_pipe % (8 * sizeof(long))))));

  ret = read(exit_pipe, &c, 1);
  if (ret < 0)
    fatal("read: %s", strerror(*__errno_location()));

  return c;
}

Function: char *pretty_print_size(int64_t inp) {
  static char output[100];
  if (inp < 1024) {
    snprintf(output, sizeof(output), "%ld", inp);
    return output;
  }
  inp /= 1024;
  if (inp < 1024) {
    snprintf(output, sizeof(output), "%ldK", inp);
    return output;
  }
  inp /= 1024;
  if (inp < 1024) {
    snprintf(output, sizeof(output), "%ldM", inp);
    return output;
  }
  inp /= 1024;
  snprintf(output, sizeof(output), "%ldG", inp);
  return output;
}

test3
Prediction: char *pretty_print_size_name_conflict(long size) {
  static char output[100];

  if (size < 1024) {
    snprintf(output, 100, "%ld", size);
  } else if (size < 1024 * 1024) {
    snprintf(output, 100, "%ldK", size / 1024);
  } else if (size < 1024 * 1024 * 1024) {
    snprintf(output, 100, "%ldM", size / (1024 * 1024));
  } else {
    snprintf(output, 100, "%ldG", size / (1024 * 1024 * 1024));
  }

  return output;
}

Function: int64_t parse_size(char *inp) {
  char *tp;
  int len = strlen(inp);
  char *errstr = "bad size. examples: 4096, 4k, 100M, 1.5G";
  char mult_char;
  int mult = 1;
  double val;
  if (len < 1)
    fatal(errstr);
  mult_char = tolower(inp[len - 1]);
  if (((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((mult_char))] & (unsigned short)_ISalpha)) {
    switch (mult_char) {
    case 'k':
      mult = 1024;
      break;
    case 'm':
      mult = 1024 * 1024;
      break;
    case 'g':
      mult = 1024 * 1024 * 1024;
      break;
    default:
      fatal("unknown size multiplier: %c", mult_char);
    }
    inp[len - 1] = '\x00';
  }
  val = strtod(inp, &tp);
  if (val <= 0 || *tp != '\x00')
    fatal(errstr);
  return (int64_t)(mult * val);
}

C_COMPILE/CPP-Programming_jigarshah-platsec/CPP_Training/samples/vmtouch.c
Function: static int wait_for_child() {
  int exit_read = 0;
  char exit_value = 0;
  int wait_status;
  while (1) {
    struct timeval tv;
    fd_set rfds;
    do {
      unsigned int __i;
      fd_set *__arr = (&rfds);
      for (__i = 0; __i < sizeof(fd_set) / sizeof(__fd_mask); ++__i)
        ((__arr)->fds_bits)[__i] = 0;
    } while (0);
    tv.tv_sec = 1;
    tv.tv_usec = 0;
    ((void)(((&rfds)
                 ->fds_bits)[((exit_pipe[0]) / (8 * (int)sizeof(__fd_mask)))] |=
            ((__fd_mask)(1UL
                         << ((exit_pipe[0]) % (8 * (int)sizeof(__fd_mask)))))));
    if (select(exit_pipe[0] + 1, &rfds, ((void *)0), ((void *)0), &tv) < 0)
      fatal("select: %s", strerror((*__errno_location())));
    if (waitpid(daemon_pid, &wait_status, 1) > 0)
      fatal("daemon shut down unexpectedly");
    if (((((&rfds)->fds_bits)[((exit_pipe[0]) / (8 * (int)sizeof(__fd_mask)))] &
          ((__fd_mask)(1UL << ((exit_pipe[0]) %
                               (8 * (int)sizeof(__fd_mask)))))) != 0))
      break;
  }
  exit_read = read(exit_pipe[0], &exit_value, 1);
  if (exit_read < 0)
    fatal("read: %s", strerror((*__errno_location())));
  return exit_value;
}

test3
Prediction: int wait_for_child_name_conflict(void) {
  int ret = 0;
  char c = 0;

  do {
    fd_set fds;
    struct timeval tv;
    int status;

    for (unsigned int i = 0; i < sizeof(fds.fds_bits); i++)
      fds.fds_bits[i] = 0;

    tv.tv_sec = 1;
    tv.tv_usec = 0;

    fds.fds_bits[exit_pipe / (8 * sizeof(long))] |=
        (1UL << (exit_pipe % (8 * sizeof(long))));

    if (select(exit_pipe + 1, &fds, NULL, NULL, &tv) < 0)
      fatal("select: %s", strerror(*__errno_location()));

    if (waitpid(daemon_pid, &status, 1) > 0)
      fatal("daemon shut down unexpectedly");
  } while (!(fds.fds_bits[exit_pipe / (8 * sizeof(long))] &
             (1UL << (exit_pipe % (8 * sizeof(long))))));

  ret = read(exit_pipe, &c, 1);
  if (ret < 0)
    fatal("read: %s", strerror(*__errno_location()));

  return c;
}

Function: char *pretty_print_size(int64_t inp) {
  static char output[100];
  if (inp < 1024) {
    snprintf(output, sizeof(output), "%ld", inp);
    return output;
  }
  inp /= 1024;
  if (inp < 1024) {
    snprintf(output, sizeof(output), "%ldK", inp);
    return output;
  }
  inp /= 1024;
  if (inp < 1024) {
    snprintf(output, sizeof(output), "%ldM", inp);
    return output;
  }
  inp /= 1024;
  snprintf(output, sizeof(output), "%ldG", inp);
  return output;
}

test3
Prediction: char *pretty_print_size_name_conflict(long size) {
  static char output[100];

  if (size < 1024) {
    snprintf(output, 100, "%ld", size);
  } else if (size < 1024 * 1024) {
    snprintf(output, 100, "%ldK", size / 1024);
  } else if (size < 1024 * 1024 * 1024) {
    snprintf(output, 100, "%ldM", size / (1024 * 1024));
  } else {
    snprintf(output, 100, "%ldG", size / (1024 * 1024 * 1024));
  }

  return output;
}

Function: int64_t parse_size(char *inp) {
  char *tp;
  int len = strlen(inp);
  char *errstr = "bad size. examples: 4096, 4k, 100M, 1.5G";
  char mult_char;
  int mult = 1;
  double val;
  if (len < 1)
    fatal(errstr);
  mult_char = tolower(inp[len - 1]);
  if (((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((mult_char))] & (unsigned short)_ISalpha)) {
    switch (mult_char) {
    case 'k':
      mult = 1024;
      break;
    case 'm':
      mult = 1024 * 1024;
      break;
    case 'g':
      mult = 1024 * 1024 * 1024;
      break;
    default:
      fatal("unknown size multiplier: %c", mult_char);
    }
    inp[len - 1] = '\x00';
  }
  val = strtod(inp, &tp);
  if (val <= 0 || *tp != '\x00')
    fatal(errstr);
  return (int64_t)(mult * val);
}

test3
Prediction: size_t parse_size_name_conflict(char *str) {

  char *end;
  double size;
  char multiplier;
  int multiplier_value = 1;
  const char *err_msg = "bad size. examples: 4096, 4k, 100M, 1.5G";

  if (len < 1)
    fatal(err_msg);

  multiplier = tolower(str[len - 1]);
  if (__ctype_b_loc().__mb_cur_max == 1 &&
      (__ctype_b_loc().__b[((unsigned char)(multiplier))] & 0x400)) {
    switch (multiplier) {
    case 'k':
      multiplier_value = 1024;
      break;
    case 'm':
      multiplier_value = 1024 * 1024;
      break;
    case 'g':
      multiplier_value = 1024 * 1024 * 1024;
      break;
    default:
      fatal("unknown size multiplier: %c", multiplier);
    }
    str[len - 1] = '\0';
  }

  size = strtod(str, &end);
  if (size <= 0 || *end != '\0')
    fatal(err_msg);

  return (size_t)(size * multiplier_value);
}

Function: long total_days(struct date a_date) {
  long days;
  if (a_date.month <= 2) {
    a_date.year -= 1;
    a_date.month += 13;
  } else
    a_date.month += 1;
  days = (1461 * a_date.year / 4) + ((153 * a_date.month) / 5) + a_date.day;
  return (days);
}

Function: int median(int a[], int i, int j, int k) {
  if (a[i] > a[j] && a[i] > a[k])
    return (a[j] > a[k]) ? j : k;
  if (a[i] < a[j] && a[i] < a[k])
    return (a[j] > a[k]) ? k : j;
  return i;
}

        return j;
      else
        return k;
    } else
      return i;
  } else {
    if (a[j] < a[k]) {
      if (a[i] < a[k])
        return i;
      else
        return k;
    } else
      return j;
  }

Function: int fib(int n) {
  if (n < 2)
    return n;
  int last = 1;
  int old_last = 0;
  int i;
  for (i = 2; i <= n; i++) {
    int temp = last;
    last = last + old_last;
    old_last = temp;
  }
  return last;
}

    c = a + b;
    a = b;
    b = c;
  }
  return c;
}

int search_name_conflict_recursion(int *array, int size, int value, int start,
                                   int end) {
  if (start > end)
    return -1;

  int mid = (start + end) / 2;

  if (array[mid] == value)
    return mid;
  else if (array[mid] < value)
    return search_name_conflict_recursion(array, size, value, mid + 1, end);
  else
    return search_name_conflict_recursion(array, size, value, start, mid - 1);
}

Function: int search_recursion(int a[], int n, int val, int low, int high) {
  if (high < low)
    return -1;
  int mid = (high + low) / 2;
  if (a[mid] == val)
    return mid;
  if (val > a[mid])
    return search_recursion(a, n, val, mid + 1, high);
  return search_recursion(a, n, val, low, mid - 1);
}

C_COMPILE/COMS10001_conorhoughton/2016_17/3_search/source/binary_search.c
Function: int search(int a[], int n, int val) {
  int mid;
  int low = 0;
  int high = n - 1;
  while (low <= high) {
    mid = (low + high) / 2;
    if (a[mid] == val)
      return mid;
    else if (val > a[mid])
      low = mid + 1;
    else
      high = mid - 1;
  }
  return -1;
}

test3
Prediction: int search_name_conflict(int *arr, int n, int key) {
  int low = 0;
  int high = n - 1;
  int mid;

  while (low <= high) {
    mid = (low + high) / 2;
    if (arr[mid] == key)
      return mid;
    else if (arr[mid] < key)
      low = mid + 1;
    else
      high = mid - 1;
  }

  return -1;
}

C_COMPILE/COMS10001_conorhoughton/2016_17/2_big_oh/source/find_largest.c
Function: int search(int a[], int n) {
  int i;
  int best_val = a[0];
  for (i = 1; i < n; i++) {
    if (a[i] > best_val)
      best_val = a[i];
  }
  return best_val;
}

  int i, max = arr[0];
  for (i = 1; i < n; i++) {
    if (arr[i] > max) {
      max = arr[i];
    }
  }
  return max;
}

Function: int is_entry(struct node *root, int a_entry) {
  if (root == ((void *)0))
    return 0;
  else if (root->entry == a_entry)
    return 1;
  if (root->entry > a_entry)
    return is_entry(root->left, a_entry);
  return is_entry(root->right, a_entry);
}

Prediction: node *add_node_r(node *root, int data, int *height) {
  if (root == NULL) {
    *height = 1;
    return make_node(data);
  }

  if (data < root->data) {
    root->left = add_node_r(root->left, data, height);
    if (*height) {
      switch (root->balance) {
      case 1:
        root->balance = 0;
        *height = 0;
        break;
      case 0:
        root->balance = -1;
        break;
      case -1:
        if (root->left->balance == 1) {
          root = rotate_ll(root);
        } else {
          root = rotate_lr(root);
        }
        *height = 0;
        break;
      }
    }
  } else {
    root->right = add_node_r(root->right, data, height);
    if (*height) {
      switch (root->balance) {
      case 1:
        root->balance = 0;
        *height = 0;
        break;
      case 0:
        root->balance = 1;
        break;
      case -1:
        if (root->right->balance == -1) {
          root = rotate_rr(root);
        } else {
          root = rotate_rl(root);
        }
        *height = 0;
        break;
      }
    }
  }

  return root;
}

Function: struct node *add_node_r(struct node *here, int new_entry, int *work_needed) {
  if (here == ((void *)0)) {
    *work_needed = 1;
    return make_node(new_entry);
  }
  if (new_entry < here->entry) {
    here->left = add_node_r(here->left, new_entry, work_needed);
    if (*work_needed) {
      switch (here->balance) {
      case -1:
        here->balance = 0;
        *work_needed = 0;
        return here;
      case 0:
        here->balance = 1;
        return here;
      case 1:
        if (here->left->balance == 1)
          here = rotate_ll(here);
        else
          here = rotate_lr(here);
        *work_needed = 0;
        return here;
      }
    }
  } else {
    here->right = add_node_r(here->right, new_entry, work_needed);
    if (*work_needed) {
      switch (here->balance) {
      case 1:
        here->balance = 0;
        *work_needed = 0;
        return here;
      case 0:
        here->balance = -1;
        return here;
      case -1:
        if (here->right->balance == -1)
          here = rotate_rr(here);
        else
          here = rotate_rl(here);
        *work_needed = 0;
        return here;
      }
    }
  }
  return here;
}

        } else {

        root->balance_factor = 0;
        *height = 0;
      }
    }

        } else {

        }
        *height = 0;
