Function: struct node *rotate_ll(struct node *here) {
  struct node *left = here->left;
  here->left = left->right;
  left->right = here;
  here->balance = 0;
  here = left;
  here->balance = 0;
  return here;
}

Function: struct node *rotate_lr(struct node *here) {
  struct node *left = here->left;
  struct node *left_right = left->right;
  left->right = left_right->left;
  left_right->left = left;
  here->left = left_right->right;
  left_right->right = here;
  if (left_right->balance == 1)
    here->balance = -1;
  else
    here->balance = 0;
  if (left_right->balance == -1)
    left->balance = 1;
  else
    left->balance = 0;
  here = left_right;
  here->balance = 0;
  return here;
}

test3
Prediction: struct node *rotate_lr_name_conflict(struct node *x) {
  struct node *y = x->left;
  struct node *b = y->right;

  y->right = b->left;
  b->left = y;
  x->left = b->right;
  b->right = x;

  if (b->balance == 1)
    x->balance = -1;
  else
    x->balance = 0;

  if (b->balance == -1)
    y->balance = 1;
  else
    y->balance = 0;

  b->balance = 0;

  return b;
}

Function: struct node *rotate_rl(struct node *here) {
  struct node *right = here->right;
  struct node *right_left = right->left;
  right->left = right_left->right;
  right_left->right = right;
  here->right = right_left->left;
  right_left->left = here;
  if (right_left->balance == -1)
    here->balance = 1;
  else
    here->balance = 0;
  if (right_left->balance == 1)
    right->balance = -1;
  else
    right->balance = 0;
  here = right_left;
  here->balance = 0;
  return here;
}

  root->parent->parent = root;

    root->balance = 1;

    root->balance = 0;
  if (root->parent->parent->balance == 1)
    root->parent->balance = -1;

  return temp;

Function: struct node *latex_print(struct node *head, char *filename) {
  FILE *fil;
  fil = fopen(filename, "wt");
  fprintf(fil, "\\documentclass[11pt,a4paper]{scrartcl}\n");
  fprintf(fil, "\\typearea{12}\n");
  fprintf(fil, "\\usepackage{tikz-qtree}\n");
  fprintf(fil, "\\begin{document}\n");
  fprintf(
      fil,
      "\\tikzset{every tree node/.style={minimum width=2em,draw,circle},\n");
  fprintf(fil, "blank/.style={draw=none},\n");
  fprintf(fil, "edge from parent/.style=\n");
  fprintf(fil, "{draw,->, edge from parent path={(\\tikzparentnode) -- "
               "(\\tikzchildnode)}},\n");
  fprintf(fil, "level distance=1.5cm}\n");
  fprintf(fil, "\\begin{figure}\n");
  fprintf(fil, "\\begin{center}\n");
  fprintf(fil, "\\begin{tikzpicture}\n");
  fprintf(fil, "\\Tree\n");
  head = latex_print_r(head, fil);
  fprintf(fil, "\\end{tikzpicture}\n");
  fprintf(fil, "\\end{center}\n");
  fprintf(fil, "\\end{figure}\n");
  fprintf(fil, "\\end{document}\n");

test3
Prediction: uint *latex_print_r(uint *tree, char *filename) {
  FILE *fp;

  fp = fopen(filename, "wt");

  fprintf(fp, "\\documentclass[11pt,a4paper]{scrartcl}\n");
  fprintf(fp, "\\typearea{12}\n");
  fprintf(fp, "\\usepackage{tikz-qtree}\n");
  fprintf(fp, "\\begin{document}\n");
  fprintf(
      fp,
      "\\tikzset{every tree node/.style={minimum width=2em,draw,circle},\n");
  fprintf(fp, "blank/.style={draw=none},\n");
  fprintf(fp, "edge from parent/.style=\n");
  fprintf(fp, "{draw,->, edge from parent path={(\\tikzparentnode) -- "
              "(\\tikzchildnode)}},\n");
  fprintf(fp, "level distance=1.5cm}\n");
  fprintf(fp, "\\begin{figure}\n");
  fprintf(fp, "\\begin{center}\n");
  fprintf(fp, "\\begin{tikzpicture}\n");
  fprintf(fp, "\\Tree\n");

  if (tree == NULL) {
    fprintf(fp, "\\edge[blank]; \\node[blank]{};\n");
  } else if (tree->left == NULL && tree->right == NULL) {
    fprintf(fp, "\\edge;{%i}\n", tree->data);
  } else {
    fprintf(fp, "[.%i \n", tree->data);
    tree->left = latex_print_r(tree->left, fp);
    tree->right = latex_print_r(tree->right, fp);
    fprintf(fp, "]\n");
  }

  fprintf(fp, "\\end{tikzpicture}\n");
  fprintf(fp, "\\end{center}\n");
  fprintf(fp, "\\end{figure}\n");
  fprintf(fp, "\\end{document}\n");

  fclose(fp);

  return tree;
}

Function: struct node *locate(struct node *iterator, int target) {
  while (iterator->next != ((void *)0)) {
    if (iterator->entry == target)
      return iterator;
    iterator = iterator->next;
  }
  if (iterator->entry == target)
    return iterator;
  return ((void *)0);
}

test3
Prediction: struct node *locate_name_conflict(struct node *head, int value) {
  struct node *p;

  p = head;
  while (p->next != NULL) {
    if (p->value == value)
      return p;
    p = p->next;
  }
  if (p->value == value)
    return p;
  return NULL;
}

Function: struct node *make_node(int new_entry, int height, int *max_height) {
  struct node *a_node = (struct node *)malloc(sizeof(struct node));
  a_node->entry = new_entry;
  a_node->height = height;
  if (height > *max_height)
    *max_height = height;
  return a_node;
}

Function: struct node *add_node(struct node *here, int new_entry, int height,
                      int *max_height) {
  if (here == ((void *)0))
    return make_node(new_entry, height, max_height);
  if (new_entry < here->entry)
    here->left = add_node(here->left, new_entry, height + 1, max_height);
  else
    here->right = add_node(here->right, new_entry, height + 1, max_height);
  return here;
}

test3
Prediction: struct node *add_node_name_conflict(struct node *root, int key, int depth,
                                    char *name) {
  if (root == NULL)
    return make_node(key, depth, name);

  if (key < root->key)
    root->left = add_node_name_conflict(root->left, key, depth + 1, name);
  else
    root->right = add_node_name_conflict(root->right, key, depth + 1, name);

  return root;
}

Function: int is_entry(struct node *root, int a_entry) {
  if (root == ((void *)0))
    return 0;
  else if (root->entry == a_entry)
    return 1;
  if (root->entry > a_entry)
    return is_entry(root->left, a_entry);
  return is_entry(root->right, a_entry);
}

    return 1;

    return is_entry_name_conflict(root->left, val);
  else
    return is_entry_name_conflict(root->right, val);
}

Function: int median(int a[], int i, int j, int k) {
  if (a[i] > a[j] && a[i] > a[k])
    return (a[j] > a[k]) ? j : k;
  if (a[i] < a[j] && a[i] < a[k])
    return (a[j] > a[k]) ? k : j;
  return i;
}

test3
Prediction: int median_name_conflict(int *a, int i, int j, int k) {
  if (a[i] < a[j]) {
    if (a[i] < a[k]) {
      if (a[j] < a[k])
        return j;
      else
        return k;
    } else
      return i;
  } else {
    if (a[j] < a[k]) {
      if (a[i] < a[k])
        return i;
      else
        return k;
    } else
      return j;
  }
}

Function: int hostname_to_ip(char *hostname, char *ip) {
  struct hostent *he;
  struct in_addr **addr_list;
  int i;
  if ((he = gethostbyname(hostname)) == ((void *)0)) {
    printf("Couldn't retrive the hostname from the machine...\n");
    return 1;
  }
  addr_list = (struct in_addr **)he->h_addr_list;
  for (i = 0; addr_list[i] != ((void *)0); i++) {
    strcpy(ip, inet_ntoa(*addr_list[i]));
    return 0;
  }
  return 1;
}

test3
Prediction: int hostname_to_ip_name_conflict(char *hostname, char *ip) {
  struct hostent *he;
  struct in_addr **addr_list;
  int i;

  if ((he = gethostbyname(hostname)) == NULL) {
    puts("Couldn't retrive the hostname from the machine...");
    return 1;
  }

  addr_list = (struct in_addr **)he->h_addr_list;

  for (i = 0; addr_list[i] != NULL; i++) {
    strcpy(ip, inet_ntoa(*addr_list[i]));
    return 0;
  }

  return 1;
}

Function: int OAHT_Hash(KeyType Key, int KeyLength, int TableSize) {
  int i = 0;
  int HashValue = 0;
  for (i = 0; i < KeyLength; i++) {
    HashValue = (HashValue << 3) + Key[i];
  }
  HashValue = HashValue % TableSize;
  return HashValue;
}

Function: int OAHT_Hash2(KeyType Key, int KeyLength, int TableSize) {
  int i = 0;
  int HashValue = 0;
  for (i = 0; i < KeyLength; i++) {
    HashValue = (HashValue << 2) + Key[i];
  }
  HashValue = HashValue % (TableSize - 3);
  return HashValue + 1;
}

Function: struct HashData *Hash_search(int key) {
  int count;
  count = 0;
  int hashIndex = hashCode(key);
  while (hashArray[hashIndex] != ((void *)0)) {
    if (hashArray[hashIndex]->key == key)
      return hashArray[hashIndex];
    ++hashIndex;
    hashIndex %= 5;
    count++;
    if (count > 5) {
      printf("hash search fail! \n");
      return ((void *)0);
    }
  }
  return ((void *)0);
}

test3

  int count = 0;

  while (hashArray[hashIndex] != NULL) {
    if (hashArray[hashIndex]->key == key)
      return hashArray[hashIndex];

    hashIndex++;
    hashIndex %= 5;

    if (count++ > 5) {
      puts("hash search fail! ");
      return NULL;
    }
  }

  return NULL;
}

Function: int Hash_insert(int key, int data) {
  int count;
  count = 0;
  struct HashData *item = (struct HashData *)malloc(sizeof(struct HashData));
  item->data = data;
  item->key = key;
  int hashIndex = hashCode(key);
  while (hashArray[hashIndex] != ((void *)0) &&
         hashArray[hashIndex]->key != -1) {
    ++hashIndex;
    hashIndex %= 5;
    count++;
    if (count > 5) {
      printf("hash full! \n");
      return -1;
    }
  }
  hashArray[hashIndex] = item;
  printf("Hash_inserted! \n");
  return 0;
}

    hashIndex %= 5;

      printf("hash full! \n");

  printf("Hash_insert_name_conflicted!\n");
  return 0;

Function: struct HashData *Hash_delete(struct HashData *item) {
  int key = item->key;
  int count;
  count = 0;
  int hashIndex = hashCode(key);
  while (hashArray[hashIndex] != ((void *)0)) {
    if (hashArray[hashIndex]->key == key) {
      struct HashData *temp = hashArray[hashIndex];
      hashArray[hashIndex] = dummyItem;
      return temp;
    }
    ++hashIndex;
    hashIndex %= 5;
    count++;
    if (count > 5) {
      printf("hash delete fail! \n");
      return ((void *)0);
    }
  }
  return ((void *)0);
}

C_COMPILE/JJUtil_harion01/datastruct_algorithm/c/string_search/BruteForce/BruteForce.c
Function: int BruteForce(char *Text, int TextSize, int Start, char *Pattern,
               int PatternSize) {
  int i = 0;
  int j = 0;
  for (i = Start; i <= TextSize - PatternSize; i++) {
    for (j = 0; j < PatternSize; j++) {
      if (Text[i + j] != Pattern[j]) {
        break;
      }
    }
    if (j >= PatternSize) {
      return i;
    }
  }
  return -1;
}

test3

               int pattern_len) {
  int i, j;
  for (i = pos; i <= text_len - pattern_len; i++) {
    for (j = 0; j < pattern_len; j++) {
      if (text[i + j] != pattern[j])
        break;
    }
    if (j >= pattern_len)
      return i;
  }
  return -1;
}

Function: int Partition(int Dataset[], int left, int right) {
  int first = left;
  int pivot = Dataset[first];
  printf("\n");
  printf("left :%d , right:%d, pivot:%d", left, right, pivot);
  printf("======\n");
  for (int i = 0; i < 6; i++) {
    printf("%d \n", Dataset[i]);
  }
  printf("======\n");
  ++left;
  while (left <= right) {
    while (Dataset[left] <= pivot && left < right)
      ++left;
    while (Dataset[right] > pivot && left <= right)
      --right;
    printf("left :%d , right:%d\n", left, right);
    if (left < right)
      swap(&Dataset[left], &Dataset[right]);
    else
      break;
  }
  swap(&Dataset[first], &Dataset[right]);
  return right;
}

test3

  int pivot = arr[left];
  int l = left + 1;
  int r = right;
  int i;
  printf("\n");
  printf("left :%d , right:%d, pivot:%d", left, right, pivot);
  printf("======\n");
  for (i = 0; i < 6; i++) {
    printf("%d \n", arr[i]);
  }
  printf("======\n");
  while (l <= r) {
    while (arr[l] <= pivot && l < r) {
      l++;
    }
    while (arr[r] > pivot && l <= r) {
      r--;
    }
    printf("left :%d , right:%d\n", l, r);
    if (l < r) {
      swap(&arr[l], &arr[r]);
    }
  }
  swap(&arr[left], &arr[r]);
  return r;
}

Function: ULONG Fibonacci(int N) {
  int i;
  ULONG Result;
  ULONG *FibonacciTable;
  if (N == 0 || N == 1) {
    return N;
  }
  FibonacciTable = (ULONG *)malloc(sizeof(ULONG) * (N + 1));
  FibonacciTable[0] = 0;
  FibonacciTable[1] = 1;
  for (i = 2; i <= N; i++) {
    FibonacciTable[i] = FibonacciTable[i - 1] + FibonacciTable[i - 2];
  }
  Result = FibonacciTable[N];
  free(FibonacciTable);
  return Result;
}

test3

    return n;

  fib[0] = 0;
  fib[1] = 1;

  for (int i = 2; i <= n; i++)
    fib[i] = fib[i - 2] + fib[i - 1];

  long long result = fib[n];
  free(fib);
  return result;
}

Function: int evaluatePostfix(char *exp) {
  struct stack s;
  s.top = -1;
  int i;
  for (i = 0; exp[i] != '\x00'; ++i) {
    if (((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((exp[i]))] & (unsigned short)_ISdigit))
      push(&s, exp[i] - '0');
    else {
      int val1 = pop(&s);
      int val2 = pop(&s);
      switch (exp[i]) {
      case '+':
        push(&s, val2 + val1);
        break;
      case '-':
        push(&s, val2 - val1);
        break;
      case '*':
        push(&s, val2 * val1);
        break;
      case '/':
        push(&s, val2 / val1);
        break;
      }
    }
  }
  return pop(&s);
}

test3
Prediction: int evaluatePostfix_name_conflict(char *postfix) {
  int i, op1, op2;
  char c;
  int stack[16];
  stack[0] = -1;
  for (i = 0; postfix[i] != '\0'; i++) {
    c = postfix[i];
    if ((__ctype_b_loc()[c] & 02000) != 0) {
      push(stack, c - '0');
    } else {
      op1 = pop(stack);
      op2 = pop(stack);
      switch (c) {
      case '+':
        push(stack, op2 + op1);
        break;
      case '-':
        push(stack, op2 - op1);
        break;
      case '*':
        push(stack, op2 * op1);
        break;
      case '/':
        push(stack, op2 / op1);
        break;
      }
    }
  }
  return pop(stack);
}

Function: int prec(char c) {
  if (c == '^')
    return 3;
  else if (c == '*' || c == '/')
    return 2;
  else if (c == '+' || c == '-')
    return 1;
  else
    return -1;
}

test3

  if (op == '^')
    return 3;
  else if (op == '*' || op == '/')
    return 2;
  else if (op == '+' || op == '-')
    return 1;
  else
    return -1;
}

Function: int infixToPostfix(char *exp) {
  int i, k;
  struct stack s;
  s.top = -1;
  for (i = 0, k = -1; exp[i]; ++i) {
    if (isOperand(exp[i]))
      exp[++k] = exp[i];
    else if (exp[i] == '(')
      push(&s, exp[i]);
    else if (exp[i] == ')') {
      while (!isEmpty(&s) && peek(&s) != '(')
        exp[++k] = pop(&s);
      if (!isEmpty(&s) && peek(&s) != '(')
        return -1;
      else
        pop(&s);
    } else {
      while (!isEmpty(&s) && prec(exp[i]) <= prec(peek(&s)))
        exp[++k] = pop(&s);
      push(&s, exp[i]);
    }
  }
  while (!isEmpty(&s))
    exp[++k] = pop(&s);
  exp[++k] = '\x00';
  printf("\n\tPostfix expression: %s\n", exp);
  return 0;
}

test3
Prediction: int infixToPostfix_name_conflict(char *infix) {
  int i = 0, j = -1;
  char c;
  char stack[100] = {'\0'};

  do {
    if (infix[i] == '\0') {
      while (!isEmpty(stack)) {
        j++;
        infix[j] = pop(stack);
      }
      j++;
      infix[j] = '\0';
      printf("\n\tPostfix expression: %s\n", infix);
      return 0;
    }

    if (!isOperand(infix[i])) {
      if (infix[i] == '(')
        push(stack, infix[i]);
      else if (infix[i] == ')') {
        while (!isEmpty(stack) && peek(stack) != '(') {
          j++;
          infix[j] = pop(stack);
        }
        if (!isEmpty(stack) && peek(stack) != '(')
          return -1;
        else
          pop(stack);
      } else {
        while (!isEmpty(stack) && prec(infix[i]) <= prec(peek(stack))) {
          j++;
          infix[j] = pop(stack);
        }
        push(stack, infix[i]);
      }
    } else {
      j++;
      infix[j] = infix[i];
    }
    i++;
  } while (1);
}

{"function":"int infixToPostfix(char *exp) {\n    int i, k;\n    struct stack s;\n    s.top = -1;\n    for (i = 0 , k = -1; exp[i]; ++i) {\n        if (isOperand(exp[i]))\n            exp[++k] = exp[i];\n        else if (exp[i] == '(')\n            push(&s, exp[i]);\n        else if (exp[i] == ')') {\n            while (!isEmpty(&s) && peek(&s) != '(')\n                exp[++k] = pop(&s);\n            if (!isEmpty(&s) && peek(&s) != '(')\n                return -1;\n            else\n                pop(&s);\n        } else {\n            while (!isEmpty(&s) && prec(exp[i]) <= prec(peek(&s)))\n                exp[++k] = pop(&s);\n            push(&s, exp[i]);\n        }\n    }\n    while (!isEmpty(&s))\n        exp[++k] = pop(&s);\n    exp[++k] = '\\x00';\n    printf(\"\\n\\tPostfix expression: %s\\n\", exp);\n    return 0;\n}\n","function_prediction":"int infixToPostfix_name_conflict(char *infix) {\n  int i = 0, j = -1;\n  char c;\n  char stack[100] = {'\\0'};\n\n  do {\n    if (infix[i] == '\\0') {\n      while (!isEmpty(stack)) {\n        j++;\n        infix[j] = pop(stack);\n      }\n      j++;\n      infix[j] = '\\0';\n      printf(\"\\n\\tPostfix expression: %s\\n\", infix);\n      return 0;\n    }\n\n    if (!isOperand(infix[i])) {\n      if (infix[i] == '(')\n        push(stack, infix[i]);\n      else if (infix[i] == ')') {\n        while (!isEmpty(stack) && peek(stack) != '(') {\n          j++;\n          infix[j] = pop(stack);\n        }\n        if (!isEmpty(stack) && peek(stack) != '(')\n          return -1;\n        else\n          pop(stack);\n      } else {\n        while (!isEmpty(stack) && prec(infix[i]) <= prec(peek(stack))) {\n          j++;\n          infix[j] = pop(stack);\n        }\n        push(stack, infix[i]);\n      }\n    } else {\n      j++;\n      infix[j] = infix[i];\n    }\n    i++;\n  } while (1);\n}","pass":1}

Function: int isMatchingPair(char character1, char character2) {
  if (character1 == '(' && character2 == ')')
    return 1;
  else if (character1 == '{' && character2 == '}')
    return 1;
  else if (character1 == '[' && character2 == ']')
    return 1;
  else
    return 0;
}

C_COMPILE/Programming_with_C_and_CPP_eshaan7/C_Programming/SortingAlgos/Sorts.c
Function: int partition(int arr[], int l, int r) {
  int pivotEl = arr[r];
  int Pindex = l;
  int i;
  for (i = l; i < r; i++) {
    if (arr[i] <= pivotEl) {
      swap(&arr[Pindex], &arr[i]);
      Pindex++;
    }
  }
  swap(&arr[Pindex], &arr[r]);
  return Pindex;
}

test3
Prediction: int partition_name_conflict(int *arr, int low, int high) {
  int pivot = arr[high];
  int i = low;
  for (int j = low; j < high; j++) {
    if (arr[j] <= pivot) {
      swap(&arr[i], &arr[j]);
      i++;
    }
  }
  swap(&arr[i], &arr[high]);
  return i;
}

Function: int searchList(struct Node *start, int key) {
  struct Node *temp = start;
  printf("\nTraversal in forward direction \n");
  while (temp->next != start) {
    if (temp->data == key)
      return 1;
    temp = temp->next;
  }
  return -1;
}

Function: int getword(char *word) {
  int i = 0;
  char c = ' ';
  while (c != (-1) && c <= ' ')
    c = getc(stdin);
  if (c == (-1))
    return 0;
  while (c != (-1) && c > ' ') {
    if (i >= 100 - 1)
      return -1;
    i++;
    *word++ = c;
    if (c == '(' || c == ')')
      break;
    c = getc(stdin);
    if (c == '(' || c == ')') {
      ungetc(c, stdin);
      break;
    }
  }
  *word = '\x00';
  return 1;
}

    c = getc(stdin);
  if (c == EOF)
    return 0;
  p = word;
  while (c != EOF && c > ' ') {
    if (len++ >= 100)
      return -1;
    *p++ = c;
    if (c == '(' || c == ')')
      break;
    c = getc(stdin);
  }
  if (c != EOF && c > ' ')
    ungetc(c, stdin);
  *p = '\0';
  return 1;
}

Function: int partition(char *arr[], int l, int r) {
  char *pivot = arr[l];
  char *temp;
  int low = l;
  int high = r;
  while (1) {
    low++;
    while (low < r && strcmp(arr[low], pivot) <= 0) {
      low++;
    }
    high--;
    while (high > l && strcmp(arr[high], pivot) > 0) {
      high--;
    }
    if (low < high) {
      temp = arr[low];
      arr[low] = arr[high];
      arr[high] = temp;
    } else {
      temp = arr[l];
      arr[l] = arr[high];
      arr[high] = temp;
      return (high);
    }
  }
}

Prediction: int partition_name_conflict(char **a, int l, int r) {
  char *pivot = a[l];
  int i = l;
  int j = r;
  char *temp;

  while (i < j) {
    while (i < j && strcmp(a[j], pivot) <= 0)
      j--;
    while (i < j && strcmp(a[i], pivot) > 0)
      i++;
    if (i < j) {
      temp = a[i];
      a[i] = a[j];
      a[j] = temp;
    }
  }

  if (i > l) {
    temp = a[l];
    a[l] = a[i];
    a[i] = temp;
  }

  return i;
}

Function: int partitionPlus(char *arr[], int l, int r) {
  char *it[] = {arr[l], arr[r - 1], arr[(l + r) / 2]};
  insertionsort(it, 0, 3);
  char *pivot = it[1];
  char *temp;
  int low = l;
  int high = r;
  while (1) {
    low++;
    while (low < r && strcmp(arr[low], pivot) <= 0) {
      low++;
    }
    high--;
    while (high > l && strcmp(arr[high], pivot) > 0) {
      high--;
    }
    if (low < high) {
      temp = arr[low];
      arr[low] = arr[high];
      arr[high] = temp;
    } else {
      temp = arr[l];
      arr[l] = arr[high];
      arr[high] = temp;
      return (high);
    }
  }
}

  pivot[2] = A[(p + r) / 2];
  insertionsort(pivot, 0, 3);
  char *piv = pivot[1];

  int j = r;

    while (strcmp(A[++i], piv) > 0)
      if (i >= r)

    A[p] = A[j];
    A[j] = temp;
  }
  return j;

C_COMPILE/Data-Structures-and-Algorithms_ngattusohw/C-Implementation/Quick-Sort/quicksortExer.c
Function: int partition(int arr[], int l, int r) {
  int pivot = arr[l];
  int temp = 0;
  int low = l - 1;
  int high = r + 1;
  while (1) {
    low++;
    while (low < r && arr[low] < pivot) {
      low++;
    }
    high--;
    while (high > l && arr[high] > pivot) {
      high--;
    }
    if (low < high) {
      temp = arr[low];
      arr[low] = arr[high];
      arr[high] = temp;
    } else {
      return (high);
    }
  }
}

test3
Prediction: int partition_name_conflict(int *a, int l, int r) {
  int pivot = a[l];
  int i = l - 1;
  int j = r + 1;
  while (1) {
    do {
      i++;
    } while (a[i] < pivot);
    do {
      j--;
    } while (a[j] > pivot);
    if (i < j) {
      int tmp = a[i];
      a[i] = a[j];
      a[j] = tmp;
    } else {
      return j;
    }
  }
}

Function: int compute_fibonacci(int n) {
  int temp;
  int a = 1;
  int b = 1;
  for (int x = 0; x < n; x++) {
    temp = a;
    a += b;
    b = temp;
  }
  return a;
}

Function: int main1(int argc, const char *argv[]) {
  int c;
  int state = 1;
  while ((c = getchar()) != (-1)) {
    if (c != ' ') {
      putchar(c);
      state = 0;
    } else if (state == 0) {
      state = 1;
      putchar(c);
    }
  }
  return 0;
}

Function: unsigned int hash(char *s) {
  unsigned int hashval;
  for (hashval = 0UL; *s != '\x00'; s++)
    hashval = *s + 31 * hashval;
  return hashval % 1;
}

Function: int uninstall(char *name) {
  struct nlist *np1, *np2;
  unsigned int hashval = hash(name);
  for (np1 = hashtable[hashval], np2 = ((void *)0); np1 != ((void *)0);
       np2 = np1, np1 = np1->next) {
    if (strcmp(name, np1->name) == 0) {
      if (np2 == ((void *)0))
        hashtable[hashval] = np1->next;
      else
        np2->next = np1->next;
      free(np1->name);
      free(np1->defn);
      free(np1);
      return 1;
    }
  }
  return 0;
}

test3
Prediction: int uninstall_name_conflict(const char *name) {
  int h = hash(name);
  struct entry *e = hashtable[h], *prev = NULL;

  while (e) {
    if (!strcmp(name, e->name)) {
      if (prev)
        prev->next = e->next;
      else
        hashtable[h] = e->next;
      free(e->name);
      free(e->value);
      free(e);
      return 1;
    }
    prev = e;
    e = e->next;
  }
  return 0;
}

C_COMPILE/tcpl-book_nothingthere/code/grep2.c
Function: int get_line(char *line, int lim) {
  int i, c;
  for (i = 0; i < lim - 1 && (c = getchar()) != (-1) && c != '\n'; i++) {
    *line++ = c;
  }
  if (c == '\n') {
    *line++ = c;
    i++;
  }
  *line = '\x00';
  return i;
}

C_COMPILE/tcpl-book_nothingthere/code/binsearch.c
Function: int binsearch(int x, int v[], int n) {
  int low, high, mid;
  low = 0;
  high = n - 1;
  while (low <= high) {
    mid = (low + high) / 2;
    if (x < v[mid]) {
      high = mid - 1;
    } else if (x > v[mid]) {
      low = mid + 1;
    } else {
      return mid;
    }
  }
  return -1;
}

test3

      low = mid + 1;
    else
      return mid;
  }
  return -1;
}

Function: int getword(char *word, int lim) {
  int getch(void);
  void ungetch(int);
  int c;
  while (((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c = getch()))] & (unsigned short)_ISblank))
    ;
  if (c != (-1)) {
    *word++ = c;
  }
  if (!((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c))] & (unsigned short)_ISalpha)) {
    *word = '\x00';
    return c;
  }
  for (; --lim; word++) {
    if (!((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((*word = getch()))] &
          (unsigned short)_ISalnum)) {
      ungetch(*word);
      break;
    }
  }
  *word = '\x00';
  return word[0];
}

    ;

    *w++ = c;

      if (!isalnum(*w = getch()) && *w != '_') {
        ungetch(*w);
        break;
      }
  *w = '\0';
  return c;
}

Function: unsigned int setbits(unsigned int x, int p, int n, unsigned int y) {
  unsigned int padding = p + 1 - n;
  unsigned int target = (~(~0 << n) & y) << padding;
  unsigned int empty = ((~0 << (p + 1)) | ~(~0 << padding)) & x;
  return target | empty;
}

test3
Prediction: unsigned int setbits(unsigned int x, unsigned int p, unsigned int n,
                     unsigned int y) {
  return (x & ~(~(~0U << n) << (p + 1 - n))) |
         ((y & ~(~0U << n)) << (p + 1 - n));
}

C_COMPILE/tcpl-book_nothingthere/code/dcl.c
Function: int gettoken(void) {
  int c;
  char *p = token;
  while ((c = getch()) == ' ' || c == '\t')
    ;
  if (c == '(') {
    if ((c = getch()) == ')') {
      strcpy(token, "()");
      tokentype = PARENS;
    } else {
      ungetch(c);
      tokentype = '(';
    }
  } else if (c == '[') {
    for (*p++ = c; (*p++ = getch()) != ']';)
      ;
    *p = '\x00';
    tokentype = BRACKETS;
  } else if (((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c))] & (unsigned short)_ISalpha)) {
    for (*p++ = c;
         ((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c = getch()))] & (unsigned short)_ISalnum);)
      *p++ = c;
    *p = '\x00';
    ungetch(c);
    tokentype = NAME;
  } else
    tokentype = c;
  return tokentype;
}

test3

  void ungetch(int);

  while ((c = getch()) == ' ' || c == '\t')
    ;

  if (c == '(') {
    if ((c = getch()) == ')') {
      _token = (c << 8) | c;
      *p = '\0';
      return tokentype = 1;
    } else {
      ungetch(c);
      return tokentype = '(';
    }
  } else if (c == '[') {
    for (*p++ = c; (*p++ = getch()) != ']';)
      ;
    *p = '\0';
    return tokentype = 2;
  } else if (isalpha(c)) {
    for (*p++ = c; isalnum(c = getch());)
      *p++ = c;
    *p = '\0';
    ungetch(c);
    return tokentype = 0;
  } else
    return tokentype = c;
}

Function: int get_line(char line[], int lim) {
  int c, i;
  for (i = 0; i < lim - 1 && (c = getchar()) != (-1) && c != '\n'; i++) {
    line[i] = c;
  }
  if (c == '\n') {
    line[i] = '\n';
    i++;
  }
  line[i] = '\x00';
  return i;
}

    ++i;

Function: int get_line(char *line, int lim) {
  int i, c;
  for (i = 0; i < lim - 1 && (c = getchar()) != (-1) && c != '\n'; i++) {
    *line++ = c;
  }
  if (c == '\n') {
    *line++ = c;
    i++;
  }
  *line = '\x00';
  return i;
}

Function: int get_line(void) {
  int c, i;
  extern char line[];
  for (i = 0; i < 1000 - 1 && (c = getchar()) != (-1) && c != '\n'; ++i)
    line[i] = c;
  if (c == '\n') {
    line[i] = c;
    ++i;
  }
  line[i] = '\x00';
  return i;
}

C_COMPILE/tcpl-book_nothingthere/code/keyword_count.c
Function: int getword(char *word, int lim) {
  int getch(void);
  void ungetch(int);
  int c;
  while ((c = getch()) == ' ' || c == '\t')
    ;
  if (c != (-1)) {
    *word++ = c;
  }
  if (!((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c))] & (unsigned short)_ISalpha)) {
    *word = '\x00';
    return c;
  }
  for (; --lim > 0; word++) {
    if (!((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((*word = getch()))] &
          (unsigned short)_ISalnum)) {
      ungetch(*word);
      break;
    }
  }
  *word = '\x00';
  return word[0];
}

test3
Prediction: int getword_name_conflict(char *word, int lim) {
  int c, getch(void);
  void ungetch(int);

  while (isspace(c = getch()) || c == '\t')
    ;

  if (c != EOF)
    *word++ = c;

  if (!isalpha(c) && c != '_' && c != '#') {
    *word = '\0';
    return c;
  }

  for (; --lim > 0; word++) {
    if (!isalnum(*word = getch()) && *word != '_') {
      ungetch(*word);
      break;
    }
  }

  *word = '\0';
  return word[0];
}

Function: unsigned int setbits(unsigned int x, int p, int n, unsigned int y) {
  unsigned int padding = p + 1 - n;
  unsigned int target = (~(~0 << n) & y) << padding;
  unsigned int empty = ((~0 << (p + 1)) | ~(~0 << padding)) & x;
  return target | empty;
}

C_COMPILE/tcpl-book_nothingthere/docs/ex/3-1.c
Function: int binsearch(int x, int v[], int n) {
  int low, high, mid;
  low = 0;
  high = n - 1;
  mid = (low + high) / 2;
  while (low <= high && x != v[mid]) {
    mid = (low + high) / 2;
    printf("low=%d high=%d mid=%d\n", low, high, mid);
    if (x < v[mid]) {
      high = mid - 1;
    } else {
      low = mid + 1;
    }
  }
  return (x = v[mid]) ? mid : -1;
}

test3
Prediction: int binsearch_name_conflict(int x, int v[], int n) {
  int low, high, mid;

  low = 0;
  high = n - 1;
  mid = (low + high) / 2;
  while (low <= high && x != v[mid]) {
    mid = (low + high) / 2;
    printf("low=%d high=%d mid=%d\n", low, high, mid);
    if (x < v[mid])
      high = mid - 1;
    else

Function: int uninstall(char *name) {
  Nlist *np1, *np2;
  unsigned int hashval = hash(name);
  for (np1 = hashtable[hashval], np2 = ((void *)0); np1 != ((void *)0);
       np2 = np1, np1 = np1->next) {
    if (strcmp(name, np1->name) == 0) {
      if (np2 == ((void *)0))
        hashtable[hashval] = np1->next;
      else
        np2->next = np1->next;
      free(np1->name);
      free(np1->defn);
      free(np1);
      return 1;
    }
  }
  return 0;
}

test3
Prediction: int uninstall_name_conflict(const char *name) {
  int h = hash(name);
  struct entry *e = hashtable[h], *prev = NULL;

  while (e) {
    if (!strcmp(name, e->name)) {
      if (prev)
        prev->next = e->next;
      else
        hashtable[h] = e->next;
      free(e->name);
      free(e->value);
      free(e);
      return 1;
    }
    prev = e;
    e = e->next;
  }
  return 0;
}

Function: int get_line(char *line, int lim) {
  int i, c;
  for (i = 0; i < lim - 1 && (c = getchar()) != (-1) && c != '\n'; i++) {
    *line++ = c;
  }
  if (c == '\n') {
    *line++ = c;
    i++;
  }
  *line = '\x00';
  return i;
}

Function: int my_htoi(char line[]) {
  int i, n, c;
  for (i = 0; ((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((line[i]))] & (unsigned short)_ISspace);
       i++)
    ;
  if (line[i] != '0' || tolower(line[i + 1]) != 'x') {
    printf("\344\270\215\346\230\25716\350\277\233\345\210\266\346\240\274\345"
           "\274\217\n");
    return 0;
  }
  i++, i++;
  printf("i=%d c=%c\n", i, line[i]);
  for (n = 0; c = line[i],
      ((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c))] & (unsigned short)_ISxdigit);
       i++) {
    if (((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c))] & (unsigned short)_ISdigit)) {
      n = 16 * n + (c - '0');
    } else {
      n = 16 * n + (10 + (c - 'a'));
    }
  }
  return n;
}

Function: int get_line(char line[], int lim) {
  int c, i;
  for (i = 0; i < lim - 1 && (c = getchar()) != (-1) && c != '\n'; i++) {
    line[i] = c;
  }
  if (c == '\n') {
    line[i] = '\n';
    i++;
  }
  line[i] = '\x00';
  return i;
}

Function: int str_index(char source[], char pattern[]) {
  int source_len = strlen(source);
  int pattern_len = strlen(pattern);
  int i, j, k;
  for (i = source_len - 1; i >= pattern_len - 1; i--) {
    for (j = i, k = pattern_len - 1; k >= 0 && pattern[k] == source[j];
         j--, k--)
      ;
    if (k == -1) {
      return j;
    }
  }
  return -1;
}

C_COMPILE/tcpl-book_nothingthere/docs/ex/5-1.c
Function: int getint(int *pn) {
  int c;
  int sign;
  int minus_or_plus;
  while (((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c = getch()))] & (unsigned short)_ISspace))
    ;
  if (!((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c))] & (unsigned short)_ISdigit) &&
      c != '+' && c != '-') {
    ungetch(c);
    return 0;
  }
  sign = c == '-' ? -1 : 1;
  if (c == '+' || c == '-') {
    c = getch();
    minus_or_plus = 1;
  }
  if (!((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c))] & (unsigned short)_ISdigit)) {
    if (minus_or_plus) {
      ungetch(sign < 0 ? '-' : '+');
    }
    ungetch(c);
    return 0;
  }
  for (*pn = 0; ((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c))] & (unsigned short)_ISdigit);
       c = getch()) {
    *pn = (*pn * 10) + (c - '0');
  }
  *pn *= sign;
  if (c != (-1)) {
    ungetch(c);
  }
  return c;
}

test3
Prediction: int getint_name_conflict(int *pn) {
  int c, sign;

  while (isspace(c = getch()))
    ;
  if (c != '-' && c != '+' && !isdigit(c)) {
    ungetch(c);
    return 0;
  }
  sign = (c == '-') ? -1 : 1;
  if (c == '+' || c == '-') {
    c = getch();
    if (!isdigit(c)) {
      if (sign < 0)
        ungetch('-');
      else
        ungetch('+');
      ungetch(c);
      return 0;
    }
  }
  for (*pn = 0; isdigit(c); c = getch())
    *pn = 10 * *pn + (c - '0');
  *pn *= sign;
  if (c != EOF)
    ungetch(c);
  return c;
}

Function: int any(char line1[], char line2[]) {
  int i, j;
  int c1, c2;
  for (i = 0; (c2 = line2[i]) != '\x00'; i++) {
    for (j = 0; (c1 = line1[j]) != '\x00'; j++) {

        return j;
      }
    }
  }
  return -1;
}

Function: int str_end(char *s, char *t) {
  int len_s = strlen(s);
  int len_t = strlen(t);
  int i = len_t;
  for (s += len_s - 1, t += len_t - 1; i > 0; i--, s--, t--) {
    if (*s != *t)
      return 0;
  }
  return 1;
}

test3
Prediction: int str_end_name_conflict(char *str, char *end) {
  char *p = str + strlen(str) - 1;
  char *q = end + strlen(end) - 1;
  int len = strlen(end);

  while (len > 0) {
    if (*p != *q)
      return 0;
    p--;
    q--;
    len--;
  }
  return 1;
}

C_COMPILE/tcpl-book_nothingthere/docs/ex/2-8.c
Function: unsigned int rightrot(unsigned int x, int n) {
  unsigned int temp_left, temp_right;
  int i;
  for (i = 0; i < n; i++, n--) {
    temp_right = getbits(x, i, 1);
    temp_left = getbits(x, n - 1, 1);
    x = setbits(x, i, 1, temp_left);
    x = setbits(x, n - 1, 1, temp_right);
  }
  return x;
}

test3
Prediction: int rightrot_name_conflict(int x, int n) {
  int i;
  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
    int lastbit = getbits(x, i, 1);
    int firstbit = getbits(x, n - 1, 1);
    x = setbits(x, i, 1, firstbit);
    x = setbits(x, n - 1, 1, lastbit);
    --n;
  }
  return x;
}

Function: unsigned int getbits(unsigned int x, int p, int n) {
  return (x >> (p + 1 - n)) & ~(~0 << n);
}

}

Function: unsigned int setbits(unsigned int x, int p, int n, unsigned int y) {
  unsigned int padding = p + 1 - n;
  unsigned int target = (~(~0 << n) & y) << padding;
  unsigned int empty = ((~0 << (p + 1)) | ~(~0 << padding)) & x;
  return target | empty;
}

test3
Prediction: unsigned int setbits(unsigned int x, unsigned int p, unsigned int n,
                     unsigned int y) {
  return (x & ~(~(~0U << n) << (p + 1 - n))) |
         ((y & ~(~0U << n)) << (p + 1 - n));
}

Function: int get_line(char line[]) {
  int i, c;
  for (i = 0; i < 1000 - 1 && (c = getchar()) != (-1) && c != '\n'; i++) {
    line[i] = c;
  }
  if (c == '\n') {
    line[i] = '\n';
    i++;
  }
  line[i] = '\x00';
  return i;
}

Function: int is_in_blacklist(char *s) {
  char *t;
  char *tmp;
  for (size_t i = 0; i < sizeof(blacklist) / sizeof(char *); i++) {
    t = blacklist[i];
    tmp = s;
    while (tolower(*tmp++) == *t++) {
      if (*tmp == '\x00')
        return 1;
    }
  }
  return 0;
}

test3
Prediction: int is_in_blacklist_name_conflict(char *str) {
  size_t i;
  for (i = 0; i < 29; i++) {
    char *s = str;
    char *b = blacklist[i];
    while (tolower(*s) == *b) {
      s++;
      b++;
      if (*s == '\0')
        return 1;
    }
  }
  return 0;
}

Function: int getword(char *word, int lim) {
  int getch(void);
  void ungetch(int c);
  int c;
  while (
      ((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)(((c = getch())))] & (unsigned short)_ISblank))
    ;
  if (c != (-1)) {
    *word++ = c;
  }
  if (!((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c))] & (unsigned short)_ISalpha)) {
    *word = '\x00';
    return c;
  }
  for (; --lim; word++) {
    if (!((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((*word = getch()))] &
          (unsigned short)_ISalnum)) {
      ungetch(*word);
      break;
    }
  }
  *word = '\x00';
  return word[0];
}

test3
Prediction: int getword_name_conflict(char *word, int lim) {
  int c, getch(void);
  void ungetch(int);
  char *w = word;

  while (isspace(c = getch()))
    ;

  if (c != EOF)
    *w++ = c;

  if (isalpha(c) || c == '_' || c == '#')
    for (; --lim > 0; w++)
      if (!isalnum(*w = getch()) && *w != '_') {
        ungetch(*w);
        break;
      }
  *w = '\0';
  return c;
}

C_COMPILE/tcpl-book_nothingthere/docs/ex/6-1.c
Function: int getword(char *word, int lim) {
  int getch(void);
  void ungetch(int);
  int c;
  static int prev;
  while (((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c = getch()))] & (unsigned short)_ISblank))
    ;
  if (c != (-1)) {
    *word++ = c;
  }
  if (!(((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c))] & (unsigned short)_ISalpha) ||
        (c == '#') || (c == '"') || (c == '_') || (c == '/'))) {
    *word = '\x00';
    prev = c;
    return c;
  }
  switch (c) {
  case '#':
    *--word = '\x00';
    return getword(word, lim);
    break;
  case '"':
    if (prev == '\'') {
      *word = c;
      return c;
    } else {
      while (getch() != '"')
        ;
      *--word = '\x00';
      return getword(word, lim);
    }
    break;
  case '/':
    c = getch();
    if (c == '/') {
      while (getch() != '\n')
        ;
      *--word = '\x00';
      return getword(word, lim);
    } else if (c == '*') {
      while (getch() != '*')
        ;
      c = getch();
      if (c == '/') {
      } else {
        ungetch('/');
        ungetch('*');
        ungetch(c);
      }
      *--word = '\x00';
      return getword(word, lim);
    } else {
      *word = '\x00';
      return c;
    }
    break;
  default:
    for (; --lim; word++) {
      if (!(((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((*word = getch()))] &
             (unsigned short)_ISalnum) ||
            *word == '_')) {
        ungetch(*word);
        break;
      }
    }
    break;
  }
  *word = '\x00';
  return word[0];
}

Prediction: int getword_name_conflict(char *word, int lim) {
  int c, getch(void);
  void ungetch(int);
  char *w = word;

  while (isspace(c = getch()))
    ;

  if (c != EOF)
    *w++ = c;

  if (isalpha(c) || c == '_' || c == '#' || c == '"') {
    for (; --lim > 0; w++)
      if (!isalnum(*w = getch()) && *w != '_') {
        ungetch(*w);
        break;
      }
  } else if (c == '/') {
    if ((c = getch()) == '/') {
      while ((c = getch()) != '\n')
        ;
      *--w = '\0';
      return getword_name_conflict(w, lim);
    } else if (c == '*') {
      while ((c = getch()) != '*')
        ;
      if ((c = getch()) != '/') {
        ungetch('/');
        ungetch('*');
        ungetch(c);
      }
      *--w = '\0';
      return getword_name_conflict(w, lim);
    } else {
      *w = '\0';
      return c;
    }
  } else if (c == '"' && prev_0 == '\'') {
    *w++ = c;
    return c;
  } else if (c == '"') {
    while ((c = getch()) != '"')
      ;
    *--w = '\0';
    return getword_name_conflict(w, lim);
  } else if (c == '#') {
    *--w = '\0';
    return getword_name_conflict(w, lim);
  } else {
    *w = '\0';
    return c;
  }

  *w = '\0';
  return word[0];
}

Function: int atoi(char *s) {
  int sign;
  int n = 0;
  while (((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((*s))] & (unsigned short)_ISspace))
    s++;
  sign = *s == '-' ? -1 : 1;
  if (*s == '+' || *s == '-')
    s++;
  while (((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((*s))] & (unsigned short)_ISdigit)) {
    n = n * 10 + (*s - '0');
    s++;
  }
  return n * sign;
}

test3
Prediction: int atoi_name_conflict(const char *str) {
  int res = 0;
  int sign = 1;

  while (__ctype_b_loc()->isspace(*str))
    str++;

  if (*str == '-')
    sign = -1;

  if (*str == '+' || *str == '-')
    str++;

  while (__ctype_b_loc()->isdigit(*str)) {
    res = res * 10 + *str - '0';
    str++;
  }

  return res * sign;
}

Function: int getlines2(char lines[][200], int maxlines) {
  printf("\tgetlines: V2\n\n");

    if (nlines >= maxlines) {
      return -1;
    } else {
      lines[nlines++][len - 1] = '\x00';
    }
  }
  return nlines;
}

Function: int get_line(char *line, int lim) {
  int c, i;
  for (i = 0; i < lim - 1 && (c = getchar()) != (-1) && c != '\n'; i++) {
    *line++ = c;
  }
  if (c == '\n') {
    *line++ = c;
    i++;
  }
  *line = '\x00';
  return i;
}

test3
Prediction: int get_line_name_conflict(char *line, int max_len) {
  int i;
  int c;

  for (i = 0; i < max_len - 1; i++) {
    c = getchar();
    if (c == -1 || c == '\n')
      break;
    line[i] = c;
  }

  if (c == '\n') {
    line[i] = c;
    i++;
    line++;
  }

  line[i] = '\0';

  return i;
}

Function: Line *add_line(Line *line, int line_num) {
  int cond;
  if (line == ((void *)0)) {
    line = (Line *)malloc(sizeof(Line));
    line->num = line_num;
    line->count = 1;
    line->left = line->right = ((void *)0);
  } else if ((cond = line_num - line->num > 0)) {
    line->right = add_line(line->right, line_num);
  } else if (cond < 0) {
    line->left = add_line(line->left, line_num);
  } else {
    line->count++;
  }
  return line;
}

test3
Prediction: struct line *add_line_name_conflict(struct line *l, int n) {
  if (l == NULL) {
    l = malloc(sizeof(struct line));
    l->n = n;
    l->count = 1;
    l->next = l->prev = NULL;
  } else {
    if (l->n == n)
      l->count++;
    else
      l->next = add_line_name_conflict(l->next, n);
  }
  return l;
}

Function: int getword(char *word, int lim) {
  int getch(void);
  void ungetch(int c);
  static int line = 0;
  int c;
  while (
      ((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c = getch()))] & (unsigned short)_ISspace)) {
    if (((c) == '\n')) {
      line++;
      if (line > total_lines)
        total_lines = line;
    }
  }
  if (c != (-1)) {
    *word++ = c;
  }
  if (!((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c))] & (unsigned short)_ISalpha)) {
    *word = '\x00';
    if (c == (-1))
      return (-1);
    else
      return line;
  }
  for (; --lim; word++) {
    if (!((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((*word = getch()))] &
          (unsigned short)_ISalnum)) {
      ungetch(*word);
      break;
    }
  }
  *word = '\x00';
  return line;
}

  int c, getch(void);
  void ungetch(int);
  char *w = word;

  while (isspace(c = getch()))
    if (c == '\n')
      if (++line_0 > total_lines)
        total_lines = line_0;

  if (c != EOF)
    *w++ = c;

  if (!isalpha(c) && c != '_' && c != '#') {
    *w = '\0';
    return (c == EOF) ? EOF : line_0;
  }

  for (; --lim > 0; w++)
    if (!isalnum(*w = getch()) && *w != '_') {
      ungetch(*w);
      break;
    }

  *w = '\0';
  return line_0;
}

Function: char *get_line(void) {
  int chars = 0;
  char *line = (char *)malloc(sizeof(char) * chars);
  int c, i;
  for (i = 0; (c = getchar()) != (-1) && c != '\n'; i++) {
    chars++;
    line = (char *)realloc(line, chars);
    line[i] = c;
  }
  if (c == '\n') {
    chars++;
    line = (char *)realloc(line, chars);
    line[i] = '\n';
    i++;
  }
  chars++;
  line = (char *)realloc(line, chars);
  line[i] = '\x00';
  return line;
}

  int c, i;
  char *line;

  line = malloc(0);
  i = 0;
  while ((c = getchar()) != -1 && c != '\n') {
    line = realloc(line, ++i);
    line[i - 1] = c;
    i++;
  }
  if (c == '\n') {
    line = realloc(line, ++i);
    line[i - 1] = c;
    i++;
  }
  line = realloc(line, i + 1);
  line[i] = '\0';
  return line;
}

Function: int day_of_year(int year, int month, int day) {
  int i;
  int leap = (((year) % 4 == 0 && (year) % 100 != 0) || (year) % 400 == 0);
  if (month <= 0 || month > 12) {
    printf("error\357\274\232\346\234\210\344\273\275\350\266\205\350\277\20712"
           "\346\210\226<=0\357\274\232%d\n",
           month);
    exit(1);
  }
  if (day <= 0 || daytab[leap][month] < day) {
    printf("error\357\274\232%"
           "d\346\234\210\345\244\251\346\225\260\344\270\215\350\203\275\350"
           "\266\205\350\277\207%d\345\244\251\346\210\226<=0\357\274\232%d\n",
           month, daytab[leap][month], day);
    exit(1);
  }
  for (i = 1; i < month; i++) {
    day += daytab[leap][i];
  }
  return day;
}

test3
Prediction: int day_of_year_name_conflict(int year, int month, int day) {
  int i, leap;

  leap = year % 4 == 0 && year % 100 != 0 || year % 400 == 0;
  if (month < 1 || month > 12) {
    printf("day_of_year_name_conflict: invalid month %d\n", month);
    exit(1);
  }
  if (day < 1 || day > daytab[leap][month]) {
    printf("day_of_year_name_conflict: invalid day %d for month %d\n", day,
           month);
    exit(1);
  }
  for (i = 1; i < month; i++)
    day += daytab[leap][i];
  return day;
}

Function: int str_ncmp(char *s, char *t, int n) {
  int i;
  for (i = 1; *s == *t; i++, s++, t++) {
    if (*s == '\x00' || i == n)
      return 0;
  }
  return *s - *t;
}

      return 0;

    i++;
  }
  return *s1 - *s2;
}

Function: int day_of_year(int year, int month, int day) {
  int leap = (((year) % 4 == 0 && (year) % 100 != 0) || (year) % 400 == 0);
  int i;
  char *p = *(daytab + leap);
  if (year <= 0 || month <= 0 || month > 12 || day <= 0 || day > p[month])
    return -1;
  for (i = 1; i < month; i++)
    day += p[i];
  return day;
}

      day > daytab[leap][month])
    return -1;
  for (i = 1; i < month; i++)
    day += daytab[leap][i];
  return day;

C_COMPILE/tcpl-book_nothingthere/docs/ex/5-18.c
Function: int gettoken(void) {
  int c;
  char *p = token;
  while ((c = getch()) == ' ' || c == '\t')
    ;
  if (c == '(') {
    if ((c = getch()) == ')') {
      strcpy(token, "()");
      tokentype = PARENS;
    } else {
      ungetch(c);
      tokentype = '(';
    }
  } else if (c == '[') {
    for (*p++ = c; (*p++ = getch()) != ']';)
      ;
    *p = '\x00';
    tokentype = BRACKETS;
  } else if (((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c))] & (unsigned short)_ISalpha)) {
    for (*p++ = c;
         ((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c = getch()))] & (unsigned short)_ISalnum);)
      *p++ = c;
    ungetch(c);
    *p = '\x00';
    tokentype = NAME;
  } else {
    tokentype = c;
  }
  return tokentype;
}

test3
Prediction: int gettoken_name_conflict(void) {
  int c, getch(void);
  void ungetch(int);
  char *p = token;

  while ((c = getch()) == ' ' || c == '\t')
    ;
  if (c == '(') {
    if ((c = getch()) == ')') {
      _token = (c << 8) | '(';
      *p = '\0';
      return tokentype = 1;
    } else {
      ungetch(c);
      return tokentype = '(';
    }
  } else if (c == '[') {
    for (*p++ = c; (*p++ = getch()) != ']';)
      ;
    *p = '\0';
    return tokentype = 2;
  } else if (isalpha(c) || c == '_' || c == '#') {
    for (*p++ = c; isalnum(c = getch()) || c == '_' || c == '#';)
      *p++ = c;
    *p = '\0';
    ungetch(c);
    return tokentype = 0;
  } else
    return tokentype = c;
}

Function: int get_line(char *line, int lim) {
  int c, i;
  for (i = 0; i < lim - 1 && (c = getchar()) != (-1) && c != '\n'; i++)
    *line++ = c;
  if (c == '\n') {
    *line++ = c;
    i++;
  }
  *line = '\x00';
  return i;
}

test3
Prediction: int get_line_name_conflict(char *line, int max_len) {
  int i;
  int c;

  for (i = 0; i < max_len - 1; i++) {
    c = getchar();
    if (c == -1 || c == '\n')
      break;
    line[i] = c;
  }

  if (c == '\n') {
    line[i] = c;
    i++;
    line++;
  }

  line[i] = '\0';

  return i;
}

Function: int strindex(char s[], char t[]) {
  int i, j, k;
  for (i = 0; s[i] != '\x00'; i++) {
    for (j = i, k = 0; t[k] != '\x00' && s[j] == t[k]; j++, k++)
      ;
    if (k > 0 && t[k] == '\x00')
      return i;
  }
  return -1;
}

Function: int str_index(char *s, char *t) {
  int i;
  char *tmp_t;
  char *tmp_s;
  for (i = 0, tmp_t = t, tmp_s = s; *s != '\x00'; i++, t = tmp_t, s = ++tmp_s) {
    while (*t != '\x00' && *t == *s) {
      t++, s++;
    }
    if (t > tmp_t && *t == '\x00') {
      return i;
    }
  }
  return -1;
}

      ;

      return i;
  }
  return -1;
}

Function: int gettoken(void) {
  int c;
  char *p = token;
  while ((c = getch()) == ' ' || c == '\t')
    ;
  ;
  if (c == '(') {
    while ((c = getch()) == ' ' || c == '\t')
      ;
    ;
    if (c == ')') {
      strcpy(token, "()");
      tokentype = PARENS;
    } else {
      ungetch(c);
      tokentype = '(';
    }
  } else if (c == '[') {
    for (*p++ = c; (*p++ = getch()) != ']';)
      ;
    *p = '\x00';
    tokentype = BRACKETS;
  } else if (((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c))] & (unsigned short)_ISalpha)) {
    for (*p++ = c;
         ((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c = getch()))] & (unsigned short)_ISalnum);)
      *p++ = c;
    ungetch(c);
    *p = '\x00';
    tokentype = NAME;
  } else {
    tokentype = c;
  }
  return tokentype;
}

test3
Prediction: int gettoken_name_conflict(void) {
  int c, getch(void);
  void ungetch(int);
  char *p = token;

  while ((c = getch()) == ' ' || c == '\t')
    ;

  if (c == '(') {
    while ((c = getch()) == ' ' || c == '\t')
      ;
    if (c == ')') {
      _token = (c << 8) | ')';
      *p = '\0';
      tokentype = 1;
    } else
      ungetch(c);
    tokentype = '(';
  } else if (c == '[') {
    for (*p++ = c; (*p++ = getch()) != ']';)
      ;
    *p = '\0';
    tokentype = 2;
  } else if (isalpha(c)) {
    for (*p++ = c; isalnum(c = getch());)
      *p++ = c;
    *p = '\0';
    tokentype = 0;
  } else
    tokentype = c;
  return tokentype;
}

Function: int get_line(char *line, int lim) {
  int c, i;
  for (i = 0; i < lim - 1 && (c = getchar()) != (-1) && c != '\n'; i++)
    *line++ = c;
  if (c == '\n') {
    *line++ = c;
    i++;
  }
  *line = '\x00';
  return i;
}

test3
Prediction: int get_line_name_conflict(char *line, int max_len) {
  int i;
  int c;

  for (i = 0; i < max_len - 1; i++) {
    c = getchar();
    if (c == -1 || c == '\n')
      break;
    line[i] = c;
  }

  if (c == '\n') {
    line[i] = c;
    i++;
    line++;
  }

  line[i] = '\0';

  return i;
}

Function: int readlines(char *lineptr[], int maxlines) {
  int nlines, len;
  char line[1000];
  char *p;
  nlines = 0;
  while ((len = get_line(line, 1000)) > 0) {
    if (nlines >= maxlines || (p = alloc(len)) == ((void *)0)) {
      return -1;
    } else {
      line[len - 1] = '\x00';
      strcpy(p, line);
      lineptr[nlines++] = p;
    }
  }
  return nlines;
}

Function: int get_line(char *line, int lim) {

  for (i = 0; i < lim - 1 && (c = getchar()) != (-1) && c != '\n'; i++) {
    *line++ = c;
  }
  if (c == '\n') {

}

C_COMPILE/tcpl-book_nothingthere/code/fahr.c
C_COMPILE/tcpl-book_nothingthere/code/keyword_count2.c
Function: int getword(char *word, int lim) {
  int c;
  static int prev;
  while (((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c = getch()))] & (unsigned short)_ISblank))
    ;
  if (c != (-1)) {
    *word++ = c;
  }
  if (!(((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c))] & (unsigned short)_ISalpha) ||
        c == '#' || c == '"' || c == '/' || c == '_')) {
    *word = '\x00';
    prev = c;
    return c;
  }
  switch (c) {
  case '#':
    *--word = '\x00';
    return getword(word, lim);
    break;
  case '"':
    if (prev == '\'') {
      *--word = '\x00';
      return getword(word, lim);
    } else {
      while (getch() != '"')
        ;
      *--word = '\x00';
      return getword(word, lim);
    }
    break;
  case '/':
    c = getch();
    if (c == '/') {
      while (getch() != '\n')
        ;
      *--word = '\x00';
      return getword(word, lim);
    } else if (c == '*') {
      while (getch() != '*')
        ;
      c = getch();
      if (c != '/') {
        ungetch('/');
        ungetch('*');
        ungetch(c);
      }
      *--word = '\x00';
      return getword(word, lim);
    } else {
      ungetch(c);
      *word = '\x00';
      return word[0];
    }
    break;
  default:
    for (; --lim > 0; word++) {
      if (!(((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((*word = getch()))] &
             (unsigned short)_ISalnum) ||
            *word == '_')) {
        ungetch(*word);
        break;
      }
    }
    break;
  }
  *word = '\x00';
  return word[0];
}

test3
Prediction: int getword_name_conflict(char *word, int lim) {
  int c, getch(void);
  void ungetch(int);
  char *w = word;

  while (isspace(c = getch()))
    ;

  if (c != EOF)
    *w++ = c;

  if (isalpha(c) || c == '_' || c == '#' || c == '"' || c == '/') {
    for (; --lim > 0; w++) {
      if (!isalnum(*w = getch()) && *w != '_') {
        ungetch(*w);
        break;
      }
    }
  } else if (c == '/') {
    if ((c = getch()) == '/') {
      while ((c = getch()) != '\n')
        ;
      *--w = '\0';
      return getword_name_conflict(w, lim);
    } else if (c == '*') {
      while ((c = getch()) != '*')
        ;
      if ((c = getch()) != '/') {
        ungetch('/');
        ungetch('*');
        ungetch(c);
      }
      *--w = '\0';
      return getword_name_conflict(w, lim);
    } else {
      ungetch(c);
    }
  } else if (c == '"' && prev_0 == '\'') {
    *--w = '\0';
    return getword_name_conflict(w, lim);
  } else if (c == '"') {
    while ((c = getch()) != '"')
      ;
    *--w = '\0';
    return getword_name_conflict(w, lim);
  } else if (c == '#') {
    *--w = '\0';
    return getword_name_conflict(w, lim);
  }

  *w = '\0';
  return c;
}

C_COMPILE/tcpl-book_nothingthere/code/getint.c
Function: int getint(int *pn) {
  int c;
  int sign;
  while (((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c = getch()))] & (unsigned short)_ISspace))
    ;
  if (!((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c))] & (unsigned short)_ISdigit) &&
      c != '+' && c != '-') {
    ungetch(c);
    return 0;
  }
  sign = c == '-' ? -1 : 1;
  if (c == '+' || c == '-')
    c = getch();
  for (*pn = 0; ((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c))] & (unsigned short)_ISdigit);
       c = getch()) {
    *pn = (*pn * 10) + (c - '0');
  }
  *pn *= sign;
  if (c != (-1)) {
    ungetch(c);
  }
  return c;
}

test3
Prediction: int getint_name_conflict(int *pn) {
  int c, sign;

  while (isspace(c = getch()))
    ;
  if (!isdigit(c) && c != EOF && c != '+' && c != '-') {
    ungetch(c);
    return 0;
  }
  sign = (c == '-') ? -1 : 1;
  if (c == '+' || c == '-')
    c = getch();
  for (*pn = 0; isdigit(c); c = getch())
    *pn = 10 * *pn + (c - '0');
  *pn *= sign;
  if (c != EOF)
    ungetch(c);
  return c;
}

C_COMPILE/tcpl-book_nothingthere/code/undcl.c
Function: int gettoken(void) {
  int c;
  char *p = token;
  while ((c = getch()) == ' ' || c == '\t')
    ;
  if (c == '(') {
    if ((c = getch()) == ')') {
      strcpy(token, "()");
      tokentype = PARENS;
    } else {
      ungetch(c);
      tokentype = '(';
    }
  } else if (c == '[') {
    for (*p++ = c; (*p++ = getch()) != ']';)
      ;
    *p = '\x00';
    tokentype = BRACKETS;
  } else if (((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c))] & (unsigned short)_ISalpha)) {
    for (*p++ = c;
         ((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c = getch()))] & (unsigned short)_ISalnum);)
      *p++ = c;
    *p = '\x00';
    ungetch(c);
    tokentype = NAME;
  } else
    tokentype = c;
  return tokentype;
}

  int c, getch(void);
  void ungetch(int);
  char *p = token;

  while ((c = getch()) == ' ' || c == '\t')
    ;

  if (c == '(') {
    if ((c = getch()) == ')') {
      _token = (c << 8) | c;
      *p = '\0';
      return tokentype = 1;
    } else {
      ungetch(c);
      return tokentype = '(';
    }
  } else if (c == '[') {
    for (*p++ = c; (*p++ = getch()) != ']';)
      ;
    *p = '\0';
    return tokentype = 2;
  } else if (isalpha(c)) {
    for (*p++ = c; isalnum(c = getch());)
      *p++ = c;
    *p = '\0';
    ungetch(c);
    return tokentype = 0;
  } else
    return tokentype = c;
}

Function: int atoi(char line[]) {
  int i, n, c;
  int sign;
  for (i = 0; ((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((line[i]))] & (unsigned short)_ISspace);
       i++)
    ;
  sign = line[i] == '-' ? -1 : 1;
  if (line[i] == '+' || line[i] == '-') {
    i++;
  }
  for (n = 0;
       c = line[i], ((*__ctype_b_loc())[(int)((c))] & (unsigned short)_ISdigit);
       i++) {
    n = 10 * n + (c - '0');
  }
  return n * sign;
}

test3
Prediction: int atoi_name_conflict(const char *str) {
  int i = 0;
  int sign = 1;
  int num = 0;

  while (__ctype_b_loc()[(unsigned char)str[i]] & 0x00002000)
    i++;

  if (str[i] == '-')
    sign = -1;

  if (str[i] == '+' || str[i] == '-')
    i++;

  while (__ctype_b_loc()[(unsigned char)str[i]] & 0x00000800) {
    num = num * 10 + str[i] - '0';
    i++;
  }

  return num * sign;
}

Function: int get_line(char line[], int lim) {
  int c, i;
  for (i = 0; i < lim - 1 && (c = getchar()) != (-1) && c != '\n'; i++) {
    line[i] = c;
  }
  line[i] = '\x00';
  return i;
}

C_COMPILE/tcpl-book_nothingthere/code/grep3.c
Function: int get_line(char *s, int lim) {
  int c, i;
  for (i = 0; i < lim - 1 && (c = getchar()) != (-1) && c != '\n'; i++)
    *s++ = c;
  if (c == '\n') {
    *s++ = c;
    i++;
  }
  *s = '\x00';
  return i;
}

test3
Prediction: int get_line_name_conflict(char *line, int max_len) {
  int i;
  int c;

  for (i = 0; i < max_len - 1; i++) {
    c = getchar();
    if (c == -1 || c == '\n')
      break;
    line[i] = c;
  }

  if (c == '\n') {
    line[i] = c;
    i++;
    line++;
  }

  line[i] = '\0';

  return i;
}

Function: struct rect canonrect(struct rect r) {
  struct rect tmp;
  tmp.pt1.x = ((r.pt1.x) < (r.pt2.x) ? (r.pt1.x) : (r.pt2.x));
  tmp.pt1.y = ((r.pt1.y) < (r.pt2.y) ? (r.pt1.y) : (r.pt2.y));
  tmp.pt2.x = ((r.pt1.x) > (r.pt2.x) ? (r.pt1.x) : (r.pt2.x));
  tmp.pt2.y = ((r.pt1.y) > (r.pt2.y) ? (r.pt1.y) : (r.pt2.y));
  return tmp;
}

test3
Prediction: rect canonrect_name_conflict(rect r) {
  if (r.p.x > r.q.x)
    r.p.x = r.q.x;
  if (r.p.y > r.q.y)
    r.p.y = r.q.y;
  if (r.q.x < r.p.x)
    r.q.x = r.p.x;
  if (r.q.y < r.p.y)
    r.q.y = r.p.y;
  return r;
}

Function: int str_cmp1(char *s, char *t) {
  int i;
  for (i = 0; s[i] == t[i]; i++) {
    if (s[i] == '\x00')
      return 0;
  }
  return s[i] - t[i];
}

test3
Prediction: int str_cmp1_name_conflict(char *s1, char *s2) {
  int i = 0;
  while (s1[i] == s2[i]) {
    if (s1[i] == '\0')
      return 0;
    i++;
  }
  return s1[i] - s2[i];
}

Function: int str_cmp2(char *s, char *t) {
  for (; *s == *t; s++, t++) {
    if (*s == '\x00')
      return 0;
  }
  return *s - *t;
}

  while (*s1 == *s2) {
    if (*s1 == '\0')
      return 0;
    s1++;
    s2++;
  }
  return *s1 - *s2;
}

C_COMPILE/tcpl-book_nothingthere/code/atoi.c
Function: int atoi(char line[]) {
  int i, n, c;
  for (i = 0, n = 0; c = line[i], c >= '0' && c <= '9'; i++) {
    n = 10 * n + (c - '0');
  }
  return n;
}

test3
Prediction: int atoi_name_conflict(char *str) {
  int i = 0;
  int n = 0;
  while (str[i] >= '0' && str[i] <= '9') {
    n = n * 10 + str[i] - '0';
    i++;
  }
  return n;
}

Function: int get_line(char line[], int lim) {
  int c, i;
  for (i = 0; i < lim - 1 && (c = getchar()) != (-1) && c != '\n'; i++) {
    line[i] = c;
  }
  line[i] = '\x00';
  return i;
}

Function: int strindex(char source[], char searchfor[]) {
  int i, j, k;
  for (i = 0; source[i] != '\x00'; i++) {
    for (j = i, k = 0; searchfor[k] != '\x00' && source[j] == searchfor[k];
         k++, j++)
      ;
    if (k > 0 && searchfor[k] == '\x00') {
      return i;
    }
  }
  return -1;
}

      ;

      return i;
  }
  return -1;
}

Function: int get_line(char line[], int lim) {
  int i, c;
  i = 0;
  while (--lim && (c = getchar()) != (-1) && c != '\n') {
    line[i++] = c;
  }
  if (c == '\n') {
    line[i++] = c;
  }
  line[i] = '\x00';
  return i;
}

test3

  int c, i;

  i = 0;
  while (--lim > 0 && (c = getchar()) != EOF && c != '\n')
    s[i++] = c;
  if (c == '\n')
    s[i++] = c;
  s[i] = '\0';
  return i;
}

Function: long long pop() {
  long long r = arr[--size];
  if (size < (1 * arrSize) / 3) {
    arr = (long long *)realloc(arr, (arrSize * sizeof(long long)) >> 1);
    arrSize = arrSize >> 1;
  }
  return r;
}

C_COMPILE/Competitive_EoinDavey/Kattis/Number_Fun.c
Function: int read_int() {
  int o = 0;
  char c;
  while (1) {
    c = getchar_unlocked();
    if (c >= '0' && c <= '9')
      break;
  }
  while (c >= '0' && c <= '9') {
    o = o * 10 + c - '0';
    c = getchar_unlocked();
  }
  return o;
}

test3
Prediction: int read_int_name_conflict() {
  int c, n = 0;
  while (((c = getchar_unlocked()) < '0') || (c > '9'))
    ;
  while ((c >= '0') && (c <= '9')) {
    n = (n << 3) + (n << 1) + c - '0';
    c = getchar_unlocked();
  }
  return n;
}

Function: int check(int num) {
  int num1 = 0;
  int i = 0, j = 0, k = 0, l = 0;
  int total[300] = {0};
  int temp = 0, num2 = 0, check1 = 0;
  for (i = 0; i < 17; i++) {
    for (j = 0; j < 12; j++) {
      for (k = 0; k < 6; k++) {
        num1 = (6 * i) + (9 * j) + (20 * k);
        if (num1 <= num && num1 > 0) {
          total[l] = num1;
          l++;
        }
      }
    }
  }
  for (i = 1; i < l; i++) {
    for (j = 0; j < l - 1; j++) {
      if (total[j] > total[j + 1]) {
        temp = total[j];
        total[j] = total[j + 1];
        total[j + 1] = temp;
      }
    }
  }
  for (i = 0; i < l; i++) {
    check1 = 1;
    for (j = i - 1; j > 0; j--) {
      if (total[i] == total[j]) {
        check1 = 0;
      }
    }
    if (check1 == 1) {
      printf("%d\n", total[i]);
    }
  }
}
